posts.description: PROTEIN ZOATS! 😍Oh how I have missed oats on my travels. They're just so warm and comforting 🤗 I know these look like a bowl of mush but they taste insanely good. If you don't know, zoats are oats with courgette grated into them before cooking. It adds greens and volume, and you can't taste it I promise. I made mine on the hob today and it made SUCH a difference. They were super creamy and delicious. I then stirred through some protein powder and added strawbs, choc shot, chia seeds and crunchy maple @pipandnut peanut butter 🙌🏼💕

Kettlebell Leg Workout 🍑 If you're short on time this one piece of equipment circuit is for you! Just complete 40 seconds of each exercise (per leg when appropriate) with 10 seconds rest in-between. 90 seconds rest after the full circuit. Repeat 3-5 times 🔥 ➡️ KB Swings - make sure you're hinging from the hips and NOT squatting down into the movement. Push forward with your glutes. ➡️ Reverse lunges - form two right angles with your knees and push up through the front heel. Stabilise the front knee and avoid it buckling inwards. ➡️ Staggered RDLs - hinge forward from the hips. The key thing here is engaging your core and avoiding anterior pelvic tilt. Keep a straight back, not an arched one 👌🏼 Click on

Say hello to Mae Perm! 🐘 She's one of the elephants here at the sanctuary. I have been shocked to learn about how domesticated elephants are treated here in Thailand - in order to make them obedient they are tortured in cages for days at a time and stabbed with hooks/hit with axes. Many of them have broken hips, mental problems or are blind - as they are often stabbed in the eyes for punishment. In the future I will never support elephant based tourism e.g. Elephant rides, elephants street beggars, elephant treks etc. I'm sorry to post about something so sad but I want to share this message with you guys so you can make informed decisions too 💕

Untensed vs tensed 💪🏻 Women think that lifting weights will make them look manly. Well, I've been lifting for a couple of years now and sometimes I look in the mirror and think "do I even lift?" 😂 When I'm not tensing I just look like an average girl and I certainly don't look "bulky". Abs vs no abs 💪🏼 A different kind of transformation for you. So many people set the goal to "have abs". I've been there, I've had them, and let me tell you ... They're not all that great. On the left I was doing cardio every day, weighing and measuring everything I ate, having bland repetitive meals and feeling tired. I found training hard as I had no energy. My periods stopped. My boobs slowly disappeared (I love boobs 😂). In all honesty, I wasn't very healthy. I didn't have an eating disorder, I just thought that this was what it took to get lean. On the right I definitely don't have abs. However, I am eating a balanced and varied diet, I am able to eat out socially on a regular basis, my hormones are in check, I can train hard, I'm getting progressively stronger and most importantly I am happy. @alexjamesritson has shown me the value of flexibility. Now training and nutrition isn't my life, it is part of my life 😊 Sure you may be able to have abs and be super balanced, but you also may not. I'm just saying, don't let abs define your happiness. Health is so much more than how lean your stomach - it's your wellbeing, your performance, your energy levels, your happiness 💕

My Journey 🙆🏼 2 years ago vs now 👊🏼 I know I haven't lost 50lbs or got super ripped but I've completely transformed my body. I've well and truly gone from skinny to strong. On the left I had just started lifting weights but I stuck to the machines and small dumbbells. God forbid I would touch a barbell!! I even refused to use protein powders because I thought they made you bulky 🙈 Fast forward to now. I've gained 10kg. I'm the happiest, healthiest and strongest I've ever been. I lift heavy weights 4-5 times a week and I do occasional cardio for pleasure. I love my body... And I'm not ashamed to say that. Why should we be ashamed of being proud of how fit and strong we are? FULL LEG WORKOUT 👊🏼 I squeezed in a cheeky leg sesh in between teaching at @un1t_fulham this morning. This workout is a killer. I was covered in sweat and my legs were shaking by the end 😂 ➡️ Banded activation ➡️ Superset: 12 KB sumo deadlifts & 15 KB swings - x4 ➡️ Bulgarian split squats - drop sets (8 reps with weight then immediately 8 reps without weight) - x3 ➡️ Superset: 10 Step ups each leg & 10 lateral lunges each leg - x 3 ➡️ Triset: 10 Reverse lunges each leg & 12 RDL & 30 second wall sit (push through heels and lift toes off the floor) - x3 ➡️ Finisher: 45 seconds on, 15 seconds off, 3 rounds: Standing banded sidesteps & lying banded hip thrust pulses 🍑 Save this workout and try it next time you're at the gym! Or tag a friend you want to try it with! Let me know how you get on! 🔥 Wearing @adidasuk 🙌🏼

THE MASTERPLAN 📚 After my Christmas digital detox I’ve come into 2018 buzzing for life and overflowing with motivation. I’ve decided that 2018 is going to be the year I make a big project finally happen. I recently looked over my 2017 goals and I realised that I had told myself I would write an online training guide, but I never did it. Last year was manic, I got overwhelmed with work and it went to the bottom of my to do list 🙅🏼 Well, this year that isn’t going to happen. Admittedly, 2018 is already even busier than 2017 but I refuse to give in 👊🏼 A dream is only a dream unless you make a plan, then it becomes a goal. So my plan is to spend a minimum of 30 minutes a day working on the guide. I’m the sort of person who loves to sit down and work for hours on a project, but that just isn’t possible with my schedule. So instead every single day I dedicate just 30 minutes. Its not my usual working style, but it feels achievable. I can squeeze it in between meetings or just get up half an hour earlier. I can make it happen. It might mean it takes bloody ages, but it will get done 💁🏼 If you have a project you want to get off the ground but you feel too busy, you CAN do it. Break it down, write a plan, make a schedule and put in the time 🙌🏼

Throwing it back to sunnier times ☀️ Guys I can’t be dealing with the freezing cold temperatures here in London ❄️ I’ve literally been shivering 😂 Seriously though, it’s super tough to find the motivation to go to the gym this time of year with the short days and chilly mornings. So there are three things I do: ➡️ Dress appropriately. My mum always said there’s no such thing as bad weather, just bad clothing choices! 😂 ➡️ Train in the morning - if I can. By the evening I have a million and one excuses not to exercise 😝 ➡️ I schedule a gym date or a class! Basically, I make a commitment. If I’m training with a friend I can’t bring myself to cancel. Looking after your body is about so much more than exercise alone 🙌🏼 I put a lot of my time into physical self-care in the form of stretching, foam rolling, massages and more. Here is what I do each week: ➡️ Prior to every workout I do a dynamic warm up. After every workout I spend a minimum of 5-10 minutes stretching out my muscles. Longer if I have time. ➡️ I get regular sports massages. At the moment I'm getting them once a week because my body is particularly tight but usually they're a little more infrequent as they're pricey. ➡️ Once a week I do a full session focusing on stretching and self myofascial release (foam rolling and trigger point work). This usually is 60-90 minutes and done on a rest day, like today. The video above is an example of some stretches I do; please bear in mind that this video is sped up to 500%! I have a selection of different tools I use to release particular tight points such as my calves, glutes and back. My favourites are my "back knobber" (google it, its epic), peanut, foam roller, massage stick and trigger pointball 💪🏼 Wearing @adidasuk at my home office 😂💗

🌟 Almond Cinnamon Granola 🌟 3 cups whole rolled oats, 1 cup almonds (whole or chopped), 1/4 cup melted coconut oil, 1/4 cup honey, 2 heaping teaspoons of cinnamon, 1/3 cup dried fruit. Preheat the oven to 160 degrees. Mix all the ingredients except the dried fruit, making sure the oats are coated in the oil and honey. Spread the mixture over a baking sheet. Bake for around 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes. Once cooked, stir in the fruit and leave to cool. 👍

Coconut Protein Bars 😍 Happy Monday! First of all thanks for the overwhelming response to my last post, I'm so glad you like it 😁 Secondly, here's a new recipe! Combine 1 and 1/2 cups oats, 1 cup @team_optimum vanilla whey protein, and 1/2 cup milk. Stir stir stir until combined into a thick paste. You might need to add a teeny bit more milk depending on the whey you use. Literally add it a tablespoon at a time. Too much milk means the base won't set! Then push this mixture into the bottom of a tray to form the base layer. Pop in the fridge to set. Combine 1 cup dessicated coconut, 1 scoop @team_optimum vanilla whey, 3 tbsp milk and 1/2 cup coconut oil (melted). Stir stir stir until it forms a paste. Press this over the top of the oat base layer. Pop in the fridge to set. Sprinkle coconut flakes and choc chips on top if you fancy it. Chop up into slices and either store in the fridge or freezer 👌 You can use the code ROSVD10 for 10% off @team_optimum products and you can find loads of recipes like this in my ebooks, linked on my profile! Am I taking up running!? 🏃 I'm the first to admit that I'm not a natural runner. Whenever I go on a jog my gangly legs resemble bambi 🦌 That being said, I have a crazy few months of travel ahead and I am going to try my very best to stay fit during this time. In the past I would have worried as I won't be able to consistently access a gym. However, I've now accepted that I won't be able to keep up my usual weight lifting routine. And honestly? I don't care 😝 Fitness is flexible. I actually think it's hugely valuable for me to mix up my training every so often and push myself out of my comfort zone. It's an amazing form of exercise you can do anywhere anytime and I want to take advantage of that 🎉 I hope you guys will enjoy my fresh content which will include travel, no equipment and bodyweight workouts! 💗

HEALTHY BANOFFEE PIE 😍 This has to be one of my ultimate favourite recipes I have ever created! Get a cake tin which you can push the base out of and line it with baking paper. For the base, pop in a food processor: 1 cup almonds, 200g dates (1 and 1/4cup), 1 cup cashews, 1/2 cup unsweetened almond milk, and 1/4 cup honey. Combine. Press into the base of the cake tin. For the top layer put into a food processor: 2 bananas, 200g dates, 1/4 cup unsweetened almond milk and 85g cashew butter. Combine and pour over the base. Put into the freezer to set. Pop banana slices on top, serve it up and devour. I recommend storing it in the fridge or freezer. For more recipes like this check out my eBooks linked on my profile 😘💕

Hi I'm Zanna and I like to train my back 🙋 Today I added in some new cardio which I thought you might want to try. Get a fairly high box and do 10 box jumps onto it. 🌟Superfood Protein Energy Balls 🌟 Just pop 15-20 pitted dates (depending on the size dates you use) in a food processor with 2 scoops chocolate protein powder (I used @team_optimum), 2 tbsp chia seeds and 2 tbsp almond milk. Then blend blend blend until the mixture forms a big sticky ball! If you need too, you can add another tbsp of almond milk to help the ingredients bind. Then roll the mixture into little balls and store in the fridge ☺️ These taste delicious and are perfect post-workout. The dates provide fast releasing sugars to replenish your energy stores, and the protein will support muscle repair and recovery. Plus the chia seeds add some extra superfood goodness 👍

Living Consciously 🌎✌🏼 I think these two words pretty much sum up my approach to life. I'm trying to be conscious in all a do. I'm not on a diet, but I'm conscious of what I put into my body. I try to nourish myself with the best quality food I can. I consciously source my ingredients; trying to buy food that is grown as locally and sustainably as possible. With fitness, I am consciously trying to look after my body. To make it fitter, stronger and healthier. To push a little further in every session. To ensure I'm supporting recovery adequately. And to enjoy the journey along the way. With my mind, I consciously choose to be positive. To be grateful. To be optimistic. To look on the bright side. I meditate. I am self aware. I am constantly developing as a person. I try my hardest to be conscious in my everyday life. To be present in the moment. To appreciate the little things. To celebrate small victories. To give my all to everything and everyone. I am far from perfect but I'm consciously trying to be the best I can be. And I encourage you to do the same 😘 Live consciously ❤️ Photo: @jonpaynephoto 📸

Surround yourself with positive people! My life has significantly changed for the better after cutting negative people out of it. Realise your self worth. You are an amazing person, a kind person, a great friend... You don't deserve to be treated like shit, dragged down and made to feel negative. Respect yourself enough to realise this and remove the culprits from your life. If someone's being negative, change the topic of conversation or remove yourself from the situation. If a friend constantly brings you down, seriously reevaluate that friendship. I would rather be alone than be with unkind ill-natured people. Find people who are supportive, empowering and positive. Happiness is a mindset, it's something you choose, and it's much easier to be happy when the people around you make you feel good 👯💕 Rant over 🙈

Protein gingerbread biscuits 🎄 250g almond flour, 100g coconut oil (melted), 3 tsp ginger, 2 tsp cinnamon and a sprinkle of ground cloves, 1 egg, 2 scoops vanilla protein (I used @myprotein) and a couple of tablespoons of almond milk. Mix all the ingredients apart from the milk, then add as much or as little milk as is needed to create a good dough consistency. Knead the dough, and then leave to rest for about an hour in the fridge. Then roll to your desired thickness and cut out your biscuits. Bake at 180 degrees for around 10 minutes 👍

Let's talk about bodyweight training. I've always been an advocate of lifting weights, and I still am 💪🏼 However a while ago I realised, sure I can lift weights but I can't lift my own body weight?! As my life has got busier and my training has become more eratic, I've had to let go of my regimented weight lifting routine. Don't get me wrong, I still lift and I love it. But I've been embracing short bodyweight workouts more and more since they fit in with my schedule. And you know what? I feel amazing. I used to avoid jumping lunges at all costs and collapse after a couple of reps. Now I can do them easily. I used to avoid burpees. Now I love them. (Yes, I love burpees 😂). I'm actually training LESS than I have in a long time. I used to be scared of reducing my weight training as I didn't want to lose my strength. However, I may have lost the ability to lift 100kg but I've gained so much more. Right now I FEEL the fittest I've ever felt. And that's a pretty awesome feeling! 🙌🏼 Wearing @adidasuk shooting with @balance_festival 🎬💗

30 Minute Leg Workout 💪🏼 This is a great workout combining weighted and bodyweight exercises to really get you sweaty and turn your legs to jelly! Basically it's a circuit of 6 exercises. You complete these exercises back to back with no rest in between. Once you've done all 6, rest for a minute or two and then repeat the circuit. Do this 6 times. Bosh, workout done! 👊🏼 Here's the moves: ➡️ 20 Jumping Lunges ➡️ 15 Goblet Squats ➡️ 20 Low Side Lunges ➡️ 15 Kettlebell Deadlifts ➡️ 10 Reverse Lunges into High Knees (each side) ➡️ 10 Squat Jumps 😜 Prepare to feel the burn!!! 🔥 Tag a friend below that you want to try this with! 👯 Outfit: my own activewear collection from @sports_philosophy and the gym is @starsgym_ 💕

Today's workout that literally made @naomilbailey, @vikkikelly and I collapse 🙈👊 We did circuits, each one was repeated 3 times. In between each circuit we did 150 skips. Everyone in the gym was staring at us thinking we were insane😂

Circuit 1: 10 burpees, 10 plank push ups, 20 high knees
Circuit 2: 10 sprints, 12 press ups, 15 mountain climbers.

Circuit 3: 12 jumping lunges, 20 froggers, 10 squat and press.

Circuit 4: 10 jump squats, 10 walking lunges, 5 walk outs.

Circuit 5: 30 second sprint, 10 clap push ups, 20 jumping jacks.

Circuit 6: 10 crunches, 10 reverse crunches, 10 bicycle crunches. 👊👊👊

Working on my weaknesses 😅 Today @mikeleept asked me if instead of gymnastics I wanted to work on squats. I said HELL NO! 😂 Why? Because I hugely struggle with them. But then I realised, that is exactly why I need to work on them. Due to tight hip flexors and a lordotic spine, it is a challenge for me to do them with good form. Plus I'm naturally hamstring and glute dominant, so my quad strength is seriously lacking. These are all things I want to tackle to become a more well rounded athlete. So? Squats are on the menu 😝 Today we really focused on opening up my hips and bracing my core. When you perform squats correctly they are KILLER. Don't get me wrong, I'm far from perfect, but I'm working on it 💪🏼 Wearing @adidasuk 💕

A bit of a different transformation - a life one: 1 year ago & yesterday💃🏼 This time last year I was setting off on a backpacking adventure through South East Asia. I had no idea what I was going to do with my life when I returned. I had graduated uni as a speech therapist but knew deep down I didn't want to follow that path. Strawberry Protein Truffles 🍓 Melt 50g extra dark chocolate and mix with 1/2 a tbsp of melted coconut oil. Then stir in half a scoop of chocolate @team_optimum protein powder. Pop a thin layer in the bottom of an ice cube tray and freeze until set. Then make the filling by mixing 1/2 scoop strawberry protein with 1/2 a tbsp of coconut flour and 1 tbsp of milk (I use almond milk). Put a teeny bit of this in each mould and then top off with another batch of the chocolate/coconut oil/protein mix. Put in the freezer until set. These are insanely good if I do say so myself 😍👌

Smoothies in the sunshine ☀️ Let's talk about smoothies for a second. Out in Bali smoothie bowls are big business. However, I only indulged in a couple on my travels there. This is simply because they tend to be laden with added (and natural) sugar. I don't tend to talk too much about sugar as I think it's totally ok in moderation. However, I think it's important to point out that if you started eating smoothie bowls for breakfast, lunch and dinner you could easily be packing in hundreds of grams of sugar a day without even realising it. One of the main issues with this is that this would be at the expense of the other valuable macronutrients protein and fats. As a result, I had a couple of smoothie bowls as treats but I tried to stick to meals which had a more balanced macro nutrient ratio including protein and healthy fats. Fruit heavy smoothies are great every once in a while but just be aware of your overall sugar intake across the day. As always, balance is key 👌🏼 Photo: @denis_plesca at @cratecafe 💕

Can we just appreciate how many gains have been made between these pictures!? (Quads, delts... Tan 😂🙈). The left hand image was 2 years ago when I weighed 63kg. I have built up a substantial amount of muscle and I am so much stronger than ever before. I never dreamed that I would deadlift 100kg or do 5 pull ups. Let's talk about mindfulness 💭 It is a huge part of my life. But for some reason I've been hesitant to delve into it on social media. I guess I've been concerned that you wouldn't be interested; because in the last I didn't care about it. If people spoke about meditation I would think "nah, it's not for me" and switch off. But over the course of the past few years it's slowly integrated into my routine. And now it's part of my daily life. I find that mindfulness (in various forms, not just mediation) not only helps me to destress, disconnect and gain perspective; but it's improves my mental clarity and also allows me to just be a better human. And I want to share that with you. So my question is this... Are you interested in mindfulness? What do you want to know? And what do you want me to share? Ultimately my goal is to help YOU. And the best way to do that is to know what you want. So drop me a comment down below and I'll be taking your suggestions on board 💗 Photo: @jonpaynephoto ✌🏼

Lemon Coconut Cookies 🍋 Preheat the oven to 180. Mix together: 1 cup flour (I used brown rice flour but I imagine almond/oat flour would work), 3 tbsp melted coconut oil, 2 tbsp honey, 1/3 cup shredded unsweetened coconut, the zest of a lemon, 1/2 tsp vanilla extract, 1/2 tsp baking soda, 1/4 cup almond milk. Mould into cookies and place on a baking sheet. Bake for around 15 minutes or until cooked through... Then gobble them up 🙊 This is very customisable - for example you could add in chocolate chips or raisins depending on what you like 👌

A little reality check this morning - you're doing great! The fact that you follow me means that you have an interest in fitness and are already taking steps to motivate yourself and make changes 😁👏🏼 However the people you follow on social media are a small fragment of the population and it can be easy to get drawn in and think everyone has abs and eats salad all day. In reality they don't - even the people you follow probably don't (or maybe that's just me 😂)! I eat chocolate on the regular and I often struggle to get the motivation to train. We aren't perfect. No one is. Fitness is my job which is why I put so much time and effort into it. I wouldn't expect someone who isn't in the industry to do the same! If you have a busy office job and a buzzing social life - making good food choices and training a few times a week is an amazing achievement. You're making positive changes that are having lasting effects on your health and happiness. Don't put yourself down and don't compare yourself to those you follow! Be proud of what you're doing and your personal journey 😘💪🏼

Early morning workouts mean I have the gym to myself 🎉💃The left hand picture is a challenge for you: bicep curl drop sets. Start with the heaviest bar you can handle and do 8-10 reps, then immediately (no rest time!) move down 2.5kg to the next bar and do 8-10 reps. Repeat this until the lightest bar. I personally start with the 20kg bar and do 5 sets so - 20kg, 17.5kg, 15kg, 12.5kg and 10kg. Have a rest and repeat twice more. I promise you will feel like your arms are gonna fall off 😂💪

Dips dips dips 💪🏼 Want to strengthen your upper body and feel like a badass? This is the exercise for you 💦 I personally struggle with bodyweight dips - I blame my exceptionally long limbs 😂 However I am building up my strength using these two variations ➡️ Eccentric dips - controlling the lowering movement. Go as slowly as possible. Aim for 3 seconds minimum (this video is triple speed) ➡️ Banded dips - use a resistance band to help you move up out of the bottom of the dip, often the hardest part of the movement. As time passes, use thinner more challenging bands 🙌🏼 Incorporating these into your strength training using principles of progressive overload (I.e. increasing the duration of the eccentric dips or decreasing the strength of the bands) will support the development of bodyweight dips. Once you can do those, you’ll be feeling pretty damn cool 😎

Remember a month or so ago when I posted the chickpea blondies picture? Well I've finally tweaked the recipe and here it is: 1 can of chickpeas (drained, rinsed and dried), 1 tsp baking powder, 3/4 cup stevia, 1 tbsp vanilla extract, 1/4 cup oats, 1/4 cup peanut butter, 1/2 cup cocoa nibs, about 100ml of unsweetened almond milk. Blend all the ingredients except the milk and cocoa nibs. Then add the milk slowly until you get a thick creamy consistency (you might not need to use all the milk). Finally, stir in the cocoa nibs and then bake in a lined tin at 200c for around 15 minutes. Leave to cool. So yummy 😍😍

Short hair don’t care 💇🏼‍♀️ Yep, I took my hair extensions out and chopped off my mop 😝 I told myself when I first got them that I would take them out after two months and I stuck to my word👌🏼 It’s extremely common to get addicted to hair extensions. The feeling of having long luscious hair is a huge confidence boost. Once you’ve had them put in, it’s hard to imagine yourself without them. I admit that I felt that too! 🙈 Which is exactly why I challenged myself to remove them. I don’t want long hair to define me, or more specifically to define my self worth. I preach about self love. I feel a responsibility live my truth and to embody my message. 🙌🏼 And you know what? The day I got them taken out I felt significantly less sassy; which is scary to admit. But it’s true. The long hair had become part of my identity and that’s exactly why I NEEDED to have them removed. Because this short haired lanky blonde is ME. Me in my natural form. Double Chocolate Cookies 🍪 Preheat the oven to 180 degrees C. In a food processor combine: 1 can of chickpeas (drained weight of 240g, drain, rinse and dry them), 1/2 cup peanut butter, 1/4 cup milk (I used unsweetened almond), 1/4 cup honey (you could also use agave nectar), 1/4 cup cocoa powder, 1 tsp vanilla, and 1/2 tsp baking powder. Once blended thoroughly, stir in a handful of dark chocolate chips. Place little mounds of the mixture on a lined tray (and lick the mixing bowl clean 😝), and bake for around 10 minutes. Leave them to cool and set - they'll still be a bit squishy when they come out the oven - then devour them 👌

FLEXBOWL 😍 "What is a flexbowl?" Is a question I get asked all the time on snapchat (@zanzapan) and here on Instagram. So today I'm going to explain it. It consists of two parts, a base and toppings. The base can be anything from yoghurt to oats, protein cookie dough, casein pudding or jelly. The toppings can be anything too! Examples include fruit, chocolate, nut butter, seeds and protein bars. 😊 Flexbowls can be healthy and light, made of yoghurt and topped with fruit/nuts. They can also be epic treats made from cookie dough and topped with quite frankly any processed crap you desire 😂 For me, a naughty flexbowl is a treat I have maybe once a week or so. It is a way I satisfy my cravings, like some people have "treat/cheat meals". However, I do have healthy ones most evenings. 💁🏼 I hope this clarifies things for you. If you have any more questions leave them down below. And also tag a friend below who you want to make a flexbowl with!👇🏻😘

Reality Check 👊🏼 These two pictures are taken 2 seconds apart. On the left I'm sucking in my tummy and sticking out my booty. On the right I'm letting it all hang out 😂🙈 If I have eaten a big meal I most definitely do not look like the girl on the left. I have to undo my belt buckles, my tummy sticks out and any remnant of abs disappear 💁🏼 I want to remind you that the girls you follow on Instagram DO NOT always look lean. (And if they do, good on them but I'm not one of those people!). They're just normal individuals with normal bodies. They choose to show themselves looking at their best and that's ok. Just make sure you take it all with a hefty pinch of salt and don't go comparing yourself to anyone you follow on social media, myself included. Instagram is only a fraction of our lives. We all have bad days, we all slip up on our diet, we all miss workouts and we all have flaws. We don't all have rippling abs and tight butts (at least I dont!). No one is perfect. Be inspired by people's imperfections 😘Outfit: @adidasuk 💕

Chocolate chip cookies! Dairy, gluten and grain free 👍 This makes a small batch. 1 and a 1/4 cup almond flour, 3 tbsp grass fed butter or coconut oil (melted), 2 tbsp honey, 1 tsp vanilla, a pinch of baking soda and a handful of dark chocolate chips. Mix all the ingredients except the 1/4 cup almond flour, then add this in if the mixture seems too thin (this depends on the butter/oil you use). Then bake on a baking sheet for a about 10 minutes, leave to cool and set, then enjoy 😍👍

7 Minute Abs 🔥 Here is the ab circuit I taught at last nights @adidaswomen event as part of a full Body HIIT workout 💦 These three exercises challenge your abs in different ways to build up total core strength 💪🏼 Bear in mind this is sped up: ➡️ Plank hip dips - keep your hips low and tuck your hips under to keep a flat back ➡️ Eccentric sit ups - quickly up, then slowly release down using your core. Aim for a 3 second lowering phase ➡️ V sit leg lifts - lift with control and then lower as slowly as possible. Keep your core engaged to avoid your lower back being involved. If this is too challenging, you can do it with bent legs, or one leg at a time 👌🏼 We did 35 seconds work, 10 seconds rest, 3 rounds total! Embrace the challenge 😝 Wearing @adidas as always 💗

Beach Workout 🌊🌴 Try out this partner workout I did with @healthychefsteph - it's based on the one I'm taking the @stregismaldives guests through tomorrow 😝💪🏼 Split the reps in half and try to complete as many rounds as possible in 20 minutes. While one works, the other rests. E.g. I did 5 push ups, then steph did. I did 10 Burpees, then steph did. Etc. ➡️ 4 beach shuttle runs ➡️ 10 push ups ➡️ 20 Burpees ➡️ 30 Lunges ➡️ 40 squats ➡️ 50 mountain climbers ➡️ 60 jumping jacks 🔥 Good luck! 🙌🏼

Back to Barry's 💪🏼 Today I was pretty much destroyed by @faisalpmafitness at @barryslondon 😷 At the moment I'm full of energy. I think it's down to my mostly plant based diet, it's got me buzzing! So I'm enjoying pushing my body in new ways. I'm lifting weights about 2-3 times a week and then mixing it up with a 2-3 cardio workouts a week. This might be a class at @barryslondon or @un1t_fulham or even just a jog around the park. I have 1-2 rest days a week. On these I spend 45 minutes to an hour stretching, rolling and mobilising my body 🤗 Please don't compare your workout routine to mine for three reasons: 1️⃣ I am totally different to you. My body, my goals, my fitness levels. 2️⃣ Fitness is my job. It is in the interest of my career to stay fit. It's very high on my priority list! 3️⃣ This is me nailing it! I hardly ever train this consistently. I've been lucky to be in the U.K. for the past 4 weeks so have managed to get into a nice regular routine. However, in June I am travelling to five countries in four weeks. Routine will go out the window and I won't be able to do classes/weighted workouts as per usual. My workout regime will completely change due to my circumstances. I'll probably be mostly running and doing hotel room workouts. Do you want me to document this for you? 💗

St Lucia Pitons = Conquered ✅ Recently, as you may have noticed, I have started to mix up my training with more bodyweight/cardio and less weights. The only reason for this shift is time. I don't have time to go to the gym so I do at home workouts or runs most days 💦 Then a couple of weights sessions whenever I can squeeze one in! 💪🏼 Honestly I hadn't really noticed a tangible impact on my fitness until today. I remember in September hiking up a mountain in Yosemite and thinking I was gonna die 😂 Today I hiked one of a similar size (and much harder terrain) and I felt fine. I could have kept climbing! 😝 I used to be scared of letting my rigid lifting routine slip but damn today I felt so grateful for my new found fitness levels 🙌🏼 It makes me want to go on more adventures! 🏞 So the lesson is - don't be afraid to let your approach to fitness change. Let it grow and develop as you do. There isn't one way to be fit! There is just the way which works for you and your lifestyle ☺️ P.s. See the views (and the sweat!!!) on my Instagram story 💗✌🏼 @thebodyholiday

Hammie & Glute Workout - No Equipment Needed! 🍑 This video is in real time so you can see how slowly I am performing each exercise. Try doing 40 seconds of each exercise, with 10 seconds rest in between. Repeat the circuit 3+ times to really feel the burn 🔥➡️ Glute bridges ➡️ Glute lifts (really focus on keeping the core tight and hips stable during these) ➡️ Single leg glute bridges each side ➡️ Hamstring walkouts ➡️ Hamstring bridges ➡️ Hamstring holds 😷 Key points here are to push through your heels, ensure your knees don't buckle inwards throughout the movements, and to engage your core - tucking your ribs under and avoiding hyperextension 💪🏼Wearing @adidasuk 💕

Nutella Protein Cupcakes with a Melting Nutella Centre 😍 preheat the oven to 180 C. Mix together 1/2 cup chocolate @team_optimum protein, 1/2 cup oat flour, 1/2 cup hazelnut flour, 1/4 cup cocoa powder, 1 tsp baking soda, 170g Greek yoghurt, 1 egg and 1 egg white, 1/4 cup milk and 1/3 cup powdered stevia. Pour the mixture into cupcake cases and then plop a tsp of dark chocolate hazelnut butter in the centre of each cupcake (I get mine from the protein works). Bake for around 20 minutes. I recommend eating one while they're still warm 😱😍 Or microwaving one later to remelt the centre 👍

📍Naked Treaties, Byron Bay 🇦🇺 Guys, the health food scene out here in Aus is on a whole other level 😱 Byron and Sydney are super health conscious. They're obsessed with turmeric, kombucha and acai. They add superfood powders to everything. Their products are labelled as raw, organic, or just plain magical. Even the smallest coffee shop will have almond milk, and if you're in Byron it'll probably stock raw vegan cheesecakes too 😂 Their brunch game is seriously strong. There are wholefood shops on every street corner. Even the convenience stores sell energy balls, protein bars and juices. You literally can't escape it! Obviously most of these things are hyped up fads but I have to admit... I bloody love it 😂 Right here I'm tucking into an iced coffee blended with medicinal mushrooms (not the kind you're thinking!) and cashew milk. It tasted like crack. I am literally living my foodie dreams. Australia... I want to live inside you 😂💕

Yesterday someone said I always look like I’m training and asked whether I ever have rest days 💪🏼 I think it’s easy when you look at a fitness bloggers social media to think that they’re always at the gym. However, I do have regular rest days. Usually 2 a week, often more depending on my schedule. For example, today is a rest day. Nutella Protein Bars 😍 Mix together: 1 cup hazelnut flour, 3 scoops chocolate protein powder (I recommend @team_optimum), 1/3 cup cocoa powder, 2 tbsp honey and 1/4 cup milk (I recommend unsweetened almond milk). Combine the ingredients and add an extra tablespoon of milk if needed. Pour the mixture into a small tined tray and put in the freezer until set. Chop into slices and store in the fridge 👌

Cinnamon Raisin Peanut Butter 😍 Chuck 250g of plain unsalted peanuts in a food processor and blend until it forms a smooth creamy butter (around 15mins). Then add in 1 tsp honey, 1 tsp vanilla extract, and 1 tsp cinnamon. Blend until combined. Finally, stir in 2 tbsp of raisins and pop in a jar! I'm sure this would work with almonds and other nuts too 👌

Hammies and Glutes 🍑 A workout with only THREE exercises 👌🏼(Give this post a like if you want me to post more full workouts!?) 😘 Supersets and trisets are great and all, I use them on the regular, but you can still have an effective workout without them. Sometimes I like to just focus on sets of key exercises. This means I can get a good amount of volume on each one, and really concentrate on form and time under tension. Here is today's leg session ➡️ Glute activation. The exercise shown here is a banded frog pump. ➡️ Hip thrusts - 8x8 pause reps ➡️ Sumo deadlifts 4x8 ➡️ Banded RDLs 3x15 💪🏼 These videos are in real time so you can really see how slowly I perform each exercise. Try this workout yourself, really using your mind muscle connection to engage your posterior chain and I promise you will be burning 🔥 Outfit: @adidasuk at @fitnessfirstuk 💕

Lunch today is lentils with roasted peppers, aubergine, red onion, broccoli and a beetroot and mint dip 😍 I've been asked a lot recently if I'm vegetarian. I don't label my diet - I just eat consciously. I care about animal welfare and environmental issues, and as a result I only use specific sources of meat, eggs and dairy which meet my personal standards. I don't buy factory farmed produce. I eat mostly plants. But NOTHING is off limits. If I want some galaxy chocolate I'm gonna have it, and I will eat meat on special occasions. I'm not doing this because I think it's "healthier", I'm doing it because I care about our planet. I'm not here to preach and I will never force my views upon you. Does every single workout have to be amazing? Do you always have to push yourself to your absolute limits? In short: no. Today has been a weird one for me. I'm in a bit of a crappy mood which is very unlike me. (But I have a sneaky suspicion is has something to do with my hormones, ladies you know the feels 😰). I woke up, went to the gym and did a few sets of pull ups. I wasn't feeling it so went home. Later on in the day I tried again and I did end up training, but I didn't feel strong. I didn't push myself. I just lifted my usual weights and didn't step out of my comfort zone. Plus, a few people said hey to me in the gym today. I consciously tried to be upbeat and talkative but I just wasn't in my usual positive mindset. Again, very unlike me. I felt kind of disappointed in myself. Why am I telling you this? Because we are all human. We can't always have the best workouts ever. Always be full of beans. Always be in a good mood. And you know what? We don't need to be. Half hearted workouts and half hearted days happen to the best of us. But what matters is that you move on from them and try again the next day. Tomorrow I'm going to wake up and put my positive pants on, and I encourage you to join me! 👯 Wearing @adidasuk 💕

My Happy Place: Under the Sea 💙 Swipe right to see the video ➡️ I want to share something personal with you. I was brought up scuba diving, I started learning at the age of 12 and it's been a huge part of my life ever since. I remember diving in tropical waters in my teenage years and being surrounded by an abundance of soft corals, glowing brightly in the turquoise water. It mesmerised me 😍 I still LOVE diving and enjoy it thoroughly - the wildlife I've seen on this trip has been incredible 🙌🏼 However I also find it upsetting the more I dive. In short: the oceans are dying. As every year passes, there is less coral and marine life. I see it every time I go down. And it honestly breaks my heart. I cry just thinking about it 😢 We have had huge global coral bleaching events the past two years and are predicted to have these every single year into the future, due to global warming, until it's all gone. Last year alone 30% of the Great Barrier Reef died. The largest living structure on earth, one of the seven wonders of the world. Gone. 🌎 If we continue at this rate the most complex and diverse ecosystem on our planet is going to be obliterated in a matter of years. My children won't get to see and experience the wonders of the marine world which I have, and that saddens me deeply 🐳 I am so desperately passionate about this and I don't want to lose hope. Please look into the issues affecting the ocean. Namely plastic pollution, global warming and over fishing 🐙 We live on this earth for free. Looking after the planet is like paying our rent. Chocolate & Coconut Protein Bites 🍫 This recipe makes a big batch! Just mix 2 cups oats, 1 cup unsweetened shredded coconut, 1 egg, 2 scoops chocolate protein powder, 1/4 cup cocoa powder, and then 1 cup almond milk. Depending on the protein you used, (I used @team_optimum) you might need to add about 1/4 cup water to help mix the ingredients. Taste the mixture and if it isn't sweet enough for you then add some stevia (this is entirely optional - I didn't add any). Then just chuck the mixture in a lined tray and bake at 180 degrees for around 20-25 mins until cooked through. Then let them cool, chop them up, and enjoy 👍

Saturday morning progress pictures - like this picture or leave a comment below if you've been following me since I used to do my "black bikini progress pictures" every week! 💃🏼 Well, I realised that I haven't taken progress pictures in months and it's about time I got back on it. It is the best way to see your progress! I always recommend that my clients use progress pictures alongside measurements (hips, waist, bust, thighs, etc) to accurately measure progress. Weight can be used and it does have its place, but it can also confusing and off-putting if you're trying to gain muscle as well as drop fat. The weight on the scales may not change but your entire body composition could shift. So yeah, give progress pictures and measurements a go 😊 P.s. Nope I don't have abs and I'm not ripped but I love my body 💕

This smile reflects how I truly feel: I'm the happiest I've ever been in my skin 💃🏼 And that doesn't just mean my body. Sure I now happily walk around in a bikini when I used to always put on a kaftan to cover myself. But it's more than that. A huge step has been my face. Which might sound crazy. I used to never ever leave the house without makeup on. Even to the gym 💪🏼 I wished I could trade my skin with someone else; as mine is scattered with acne scars and just doesn't "glow" 👱🏼‍♀️ However, now I spend most days without a scrap of makeup on. And I feel confident and happy. My skin hasn't changed but I've just accepted it as part of me. I honestly don't even think about it. I go to meetings and dinners without makeup. Because I truly love myself as I am 🙌🏼 However, that being said, social media makes self-love seem like the norm. I wish it was, but it isn't. So please don't ever feel bad if you do have insecurities, because that's natural in our society. And confidence doesn't come overnight. Just take some time to work on loving yourself, gently, because it's the best thing you'll ever do 💗

Amen! 🙏🙌 I feel like a lot of fitspiration pictures and/or quotes which are meant to be motivational can actually make you feel like shit. They say that "fit" girls have the best looking bodies when that is entirely subjective. They say that there's no good excuse to not workout when in fact you might have a perfectly valid one. They tell you that you need willpower of steel and to avoid all treats when that can lead to feelings of restriction and potentially binging. They make it seem like everyone has to train a certain amount and eat a certain way to achieve health when everyone had their own version of "healthy". Look at fitspiration online but take it with a pinch of salt. Remember to put things in the context of your own life and find your own balance - don't be harsh on yourself, no one is perfect💕

Ibiza, it's been a pleasure ☀️ What an incredible week. This is the most relaxed I've been in over two years. I don't know about you guys but I often get overwhelmed by the sheer quantity and intensity of my workload. I usually cope with this by just working harder and longer. But this isn't sustainable. We are human and we have our limits. On this trip, I've actually switched off. No vlogging. No blogging. No emails. I've only opened my laptop once and it felt fantastic. For the first few days I admittedly got a bit anxious as I'm so used to being "on it". Taking a step back was scary, as silly as that sounds 🙈 But it was exactly what I needed and I'm so SO glad I did it. Not only was I truly able to enjoy my holiday, this beautiful island and quality time with my friends. But I was able to give myself some real headspace. Time to think. To absorb. To reflect. And I'm coming back feeling not only more motivated, but more grateful than ever before. I'm truly at peace and I'm ready to return to the UK and spread some positive vibes 🙌🏼 Dress: a boutique in Byron Bay 💗

Pre-workout Flow ✌🏼 Yesterday @thestrengthtemple took me through this movement series to help open up my hips and shoulders for our workout. These are my two tightest areas and are highly likely to be tight for you too! Here are some key points Richie noted: ➡️ In the squat position, push your legs wide to really open through the hips ➡️ Use your breath throughout the sequence - nice deep inhalations and exhalations ➡️ Be conscious in each stage of the movement, trying to open up your body a little more with each repetition 👌🏼 Try repeating this anywhere from 5-10 times before a workout. By increasing blood flow to the muscles and joints you will be using you will not only reduce the risk of injury but also help to support optimal performance! 💪🏼 I will also be utilising this little combo on my layover today between flights to Australia - to loosen up my joints after sitting down for so long! ✈️🌎 Wearing @adidasuk 💕

Apple and Cinnamon Bake 🍎 This is super versatile and can be made into muffins, a tray bake, or a bread depending on what you fancy! Mix together: 1 small apple diced very finely, 1 cup almond flour, 2 tbsp coconut flour, 1 heaping tablespoon of cinnamon, 2 eggs, 1 tsp baking soda, 2 tbsp coconut oil (melted) and 2 tbsp sweetener (I suggest honey, agave nectar, or maple syrup) 🍯Combine the ingredients and then pop into whatever tray you want I.e. Muffin cases, a large baking tray or a loaf tin. Then bake at 180 degrees until cooked through. This is around 15 minutes for muffins and tray bakes, and 30 minutes for loafs- but keep your eye on it! ☺️👍

The staggered stance single leg Romanian deadlift 👊🏼 The most common variation of a conventional Romanian deadlift is to do it single legged. However, this can be particularly challenging if you are still developing core stability and hip/hamstring mobility. Enter the staggered stance 💁🏼 This variation allows you to target the posterior chain on the front leg while maintaining a smooth hip hinge with minimal hip rotation. This means you can often go heavier as instead of focusing on not falling over, you can focus on strength, form and activation of the correct muscles 🤗 Single leg RDLs are an amazing exercise for your posterior chain (which includes everyone's favourites, the hamstrings and glutes 🍑) as well as for your core. If you're new to them then definitely try this variation to ease yourself into it. Also, if you've been lifting for ages, this is still a challenging exercise as it is a different movement pattern to what your body is used to; plus you can go heavier! It gives me serious DOMS! 😝💕

Hamstring & Glute Superset 🍑 I love putting these two exercises together, it's killer! 🔥 A superset is two exercises back to back with no rest. It challenges your body and raises your heart rate! 👊🏼 Here we have: Romanian Deadlifts (10-12 slow reps - this video is sped up) and Reverse Lunges (10-12 reps per leg) 😅 Try adding this into your next leg day. I find that doing the RDLs first helps me to engage my hamstrings and glutes during the lunges 🤗 Wearing @adidasuk 💗

Lower Body Workout 🍑 Short on time and equipment? This workout just needs a barbell and some motivation 😜 Give it a go ➡️ Barbell Squats ➡️ Barbell RDLs ➡️ Barbell Curtsey Lunges 🔥 Complete 12 reps per exercise, back to back. Rest 1 Minute and repeat 5 times. Legs = dead 💀

Raspberry Coconut Protein Loaf 😍 Preheat the oven to 190c. In a bowl mix together: 1 cup oats, 1 cup almond flour, 2 scoops vanilla @team_optimum whey (use the code ROSVD10 for 10% off), 1 tsp baking powder, 1/4 cup almond milk, 1/2 cup coconut sugar, 1/2 cup melted coconut oil, 4 eggs, and 1/2 cup desiccated coconut. Once combined stir though 1 and 1/2 cups frozen raspberries. Pour the batter into a large lined loaf tin and pop some raspberries on top for decoration. Bake for 30 minutes. Then remove from the oven and cover in tin foil. Bake for a further 20-30 minutes until a toothpick comes out clean. Let it cool, slice it up and have it with a cup of tea 😊👌

So it's the last day of 2014... What a year! Honestly, 2014 has been the best year of my life by far! This year I put myself first and worked hard towards my goals. I've graduated with a first class degree, got sponsored by @team_optimum, and backpacked through Asia. But more importantly, I've met incredible new people and made some of the best friends I could ask for. I'm honestly the most happy I have ever been, and a lot of that is to do with my mindset and the positive people I surround myself with👌 2015 is a new year full of new opportunities. If I told you that 10 years from now your life would be the same, you wouldn't like it, so why be afraid of change? Implement and make the changes you want and need to get where you want to be! This is the time to move forward towards your goals. Prioritise your happiness, remove negative things from your life and surround yourself with positive people. 2015 can be your year, but only if you make it be! You can choose to be happy and to be successful, the power is in your hands. Happy New Year and make 2015 a good one 💕

Reality check 👊🏼 Same girl, same body. Different lighting & different poses 💃🏼 If you see me in person, I don't walk around looking shredded with my abs popping out 😂 I could just choose to post the photo on the right. And pretend like I always look like that. But that would be lying. I don't. In my daily life I look like the girl on the left. No filter. No flexing. No flattering lighting. Just me. And I like I look healthy, strong and confident. I love my body on the left, and I love it on the right. It's the same body, it's mine and I'm proud of it. However, I just want to let you know that I'm human. I don't strut around looking like a shredded athlete. I only see my abs in the morning, with certain lighting, and a sly lift of the boobs 😂 So please don't compare yourself to pictures you see online. It's probably the most flattering photo of the 50 we took. Us bloggers don't look like that all the time 😝 Wearing @adidasuk 💕

Glute Activation 🍑 This move is an incredible way to fire up your booty and get it ready for exercise! Why activate your glutes? It ensures they engage during your training. This supports your posture and posterior chain, but also helps to grow a peachy tush 😝 This is one of my favourites: a single leg 1 + 1/4 rep incline glute Bridge. It isolates like nothing else, so feel free to add it to the end of your workouts too to finish off your ass 😂 How many reps? Until it burns like fire 🔥 Wearing @adidasuk 💕

Breakfast Porn 😍 Right here we have a mountain of protein zoats topped with raspberries and @musclefooduk chocolate 👌🏼 If you've never tried zoats then you're missing out. It's basically oats with grated courgette cooked through them. This gives you a serving of greens and increases the volume of your food, and you can't taste it! 🤗 I have a step by step video on how to make them on my YouTube channel! 😘💕

1/4 Rep Ladders 🔥 A super tough technique I was taught by @adamwillis_lbp 💪🏼 This is how you do it: Complete one rep. Then on the next, had a half rep at the bottom. On the next, add two half reps at the bottom. On the next, add three. And so on. Until around 8-10 reps. Sound simple? It will literally leave you shaking! 😝 I like to use this on body weight split squats, as seen in the video above, but also with other exercises such as shoulder presses! 🙌🏼 They're in my full leg workout I posted yesterday too! Give them a go and let me know how you get on 💃🏼 Wearing @adidasuk at @easygym 💗

| Happiness | It's so highly sought after and everyone has their own opinion on how to achieve it. Here's mine. I've experienced unhappiness in the past. I've had tough times at school and university. I remember lying awake at night analysing my behaviour. Wondering why everyone excluded me and what was wrong with me. I was drowning myself in self-doubt. I told myself I would be happy when I was liked or when I was popular. That never worked out. When did I actually find happiness? When I truly and unapologetically accepted myself. And when I accepted that not everyone is going to like me. I had attached so much of my happiness to other people's opinions. But once I took it into my own hands, acknowledged my own worth, and started to value myself. That's when my mindset completely changed. I realised that you can't control what others think of you, but you can choose how you think about yourself. I chose to think positively and I never looked back 😊 Photo: @jonpaynephoto 💕

10 Minute Abs 🔥 Try adding this core challenge onto the end of your workout today! Keep your lower back firmly pushed into the floor throughout all exercises: ➡️ Hollow body hold ➡️ Hollow body crunches ➡️ Hollow body leg drops ➡️ Bicycle crunches 💪🏼 Do 30 seconds of each exercise back to back. Booty building with @alunageorge 🍑 Here are some simple banded glute activation exercises you can use before your workouts ➡️ Side steps ➡️ Single leg pulses ➡️ Double leg pulses. Complete 30 seconds of each exercise for 2-3 rounds until you feel the BURNNN🔥 Why do we do this? The vast majority of us has sleepy weak glutes (bum cheeks) because we spend our days sat on them! They are one of the biggest muscles in our body so it is vital that we strengthen them 🙌🏼 Often our quads take over in our training sessions; so by firing up your glutes pre-workout it helps to ensure they are engaged so they can grow, develop and strengthen. I've used these with @Alunageorge to support her performing... and also to help pump up her peach 🍑😂 Wearing @adidasuk at @performanceground 👌🏼

Fruit and Nut Cookies 🍪
Preheat the oven to 180c/350f.
Mix in a bowl:
1 and 1/4 cup almond flour, 3 tbsp grass fed butter or coconut oil, 2 tbsp honey, 1 tsp vanilla, a pinch of baking soda, 2 tbsp dark chocolate chips and 3/4 cup mixed dried fruit and nuts.
Once the mixture is combined pop little mounds of the it onto a baking sheet. Bake for around 10-15 minutes. They'll still be squidgy when they come out the oven to leave them to cool and set. 👌 More recipes like this are available in my two ebooks! Amen 🙏🏼🙌🏼 When I was at university I tried every "diet" under the sun from low carb to paleo and everything in between. It lead to a cycle of weight loss followed by weight gain as I couldn't stick to my meal plans. They were boring, unenjoyable and restrictive. The real lasting progress was made once I stopped with the bullshit diets and focused on HEALTH! I switched low calorie weight watchers meals and processed "light" snack bars for good old meat, veggies and complex carbs. I fuelled my body with nutrient dense whole foods and stopped cutting out everything and anything. I finally managed to consistently stick to a balanced lifestyle and I had the energy to smash my workouts. As a result my body transformed in front of my eyes from "skinny fat" to strong and fit. And the best part of all? I was enjoying the journey and I still do years later. Sure I've learnt even more since then but I've managed to maintain a balanced approach to fitness and nutrition because I've ditched the fad diets and adopted lasting changes I can stick with for life. I promise you that being "healthy" doesn't make you feel tired and deprived. A balanced lifestyle energises you and allows you to eat nutrient dense foods in abundance! Tag a friend below who needs to hear this! 👯 I am sharing my complete guide to achieving a balanced lifestyle in my book

Quinoa & Beetroot Salad 🥗A high protein vegan meal 💪🏼 The base is ➡️ Cooked edamame beans ➡️ Toasted almonds ➡️ Cooked tricolour @aldiuk quinoa ➡️ Grated beetroot ➡️ Grated carrot ➡️ Baby spinach ➡️ Optional: chopped avocado 😋 Then the dressing is ➡️ Apple cider vinegar ➡️ Fresh lime juice ➡️ Dijon mustard ➡️ Maple syrup ➡️ Salt & pepper 👍🏼 I don't use measurements when I cook as I like to just throw things together but DAYUMMM this was good! 😍 Its super quick to make, packed full of fibre and the edamame and @aldiuk mean it's high in plant based protein too 🙌🏼💗

Rocky Road Protein Truffles 😍 I just came back from an early morning training session and fancied having my post-workout protein in truffle form, so whipped up these! ☺️ Mix together: 1 scoop @team_optimum rocky road protein powder, 2 tbsp coconut flour, 1 tbsp cocoa powder and 3 tbsp almond milk. Stir stir stir until it forms a paste and then mould this into balls. Roll these in unsweetened shredded coconut and devour them 😝 This makes 4 large truffles each being 48 calories, 7g protein, 3g carbs and 1g fat 👌

Chin Ups 👊🏼 One of my biggest fitness goals was being able to achieve this challenging exercise and it feels amazing to control my own body weight. I am pretty heavy with long levers so it's tough for me. I can currently do 5 in a row with a full range of motion (I see an awful lot of people half-repping. I could probably do 10+ reps if I did that! 😂🙈). When you're training for chin ups - make sure you're working on building strength at every point in this exercise - not just the top of the movement. This will not only allow you to complete the exercise with good form but also develop even more muscular strength throughout your back, biceps and core 👊🏼 There is a full guide to developing pull ups & chin ups in my book which is linked on my profile 😉😘💕

Chocolate Banana Peanut Butter Protein Shake 😍 (no protein powder!) 👌🏼 Guys this shake is SO creamy, satisfying and refreshing! Best of all? It's super simple. Here we go 😊 Ingredients: 1 frozen banana, 1.5 tbsp cocoa powder, 2 pitted medjool dates, 7 tbsp @twochicksproducts egg whites, 1 tbsp natural peanut butter, 200ml milk of your choice and a handful of ice 💁🏼 Method: Just pop everything into a blender and combine until smooth. Serve in a glass or mason jar for extra prettiness. Devour in 10 seconds flat! 😂🙈

Vegan Chocolate Peanut Butter Protein Zoats 😍 I don't use exact measurements - I just eyeball my recipes but here is a rough guide 🙌🏼 Cook 1/2 a grated courgette with oats and @oatly oat milk in a pan. Add sweetener to taste. Once warmed through and thickened take off the heat and stir through chocolate peanut butter vegan protein (I used @awesomesupps). Serve in a bowl and add toppings: I added @pipandnut crunchy maple peanut butter and some homemade vegan chocolate 🍫 Why add courgette? You can't taste it and it gives you a portion of greens 😋 Tag me if you try this! 💗

German Volume Training 💪🏼 My new program from @awillis1515 and @alexjamesritson includes GVT on Romanian deadlifts (as seen in the video above). GVT is a high volume training program designed to shock the body into muscle growth. You choose an exercise to focus on and do 10 sets of 10 reps on a certain weight. In the beginning the weight will feel fairly moderate but by the last few sets you're struggling significantly 😅 You need to be in a caloric maintenance or surplus for this to truly be effective at stimulating muscle growth. We are using it on Romanian deadlifts as they engage the hamstrings and glutes - two areas I want to build upon 🍑 My leggings are @hipandhealthy and top/bra are @activeinstyle - for an exclusive active in style discount code, check out my brand new YouTube video! Chocolate Caramel Peanut Butter 😍 I just blended 250g of raw plain peanuts until they became a smooth butter (it took about 15 minutes). They first become ground peanuts, then form a ball, and then the oils are released and the ball breaks down into a butter. Then I added 50g of melted 90% lindt dark chocolate and a teaspoon of caramel extract, and pulsed the blender a few times until it was thoroughly combined. I'm storing it at room temperature so it is easy to spread 👌

Dark Chocolate Protein Bars 😍 Mix together 1 cup coconut flour, 4 scoops @team_optimum chocolate protein powder, 2 tbsp honey, 1/3 cup powdered sweetener (like stevia), and 1 cup water. Press the mixture down into a small baking tray and then pour over melted dark chocolate (around 50g). Pop in the freezer to set, chop them up and store them in the fridge 👌 If you want more recipes like this check out my eBook (link on my profile), and if you want 10% off @team_optimum products use the code ROSVD10 😉

Strawberry Breakfast Muffins 🍓 Although these aren't that pretty, they're gluten free and absolutely delicious! They would be perfect for breakfast but could be eaten anytime 👌 Preheat the oven to 180 degrees C. Mix together in a bowl: 2 cups gluten free oats, 1 cup natural Greek yoghurt, 1/3 cup powdered sweetener (I used stevia), 2 eggs, and 1/2 a tsp baking powder. Once combined, gently stir in 1 cup of chopped strawberries. Then spray your muffin trays/liners with cooking spray (to prevent sticking) and pop the mixture in. Pop some more strawberry chunks on top if you want. Bake in the oven for about 20 minutes - keep an eye on them. This recipe makes 6 big muffins or around 9 medium muffins. You could change the fruit to other berries ☺️👍

What is my workout routine?! 🤔 Recently I've had a lot of people ask me about how I train. I reply honestly: it varies hugely. Right now I'm probably training 4 times a week for 45 minutes to an hour with a mix of weight training, bodyweight training and HIIT 💪🏼 The usual response is: "Woah, I thought as a fitness blogger you would train hours every single day" 😱 Nahhh mate. I literally haven't got time for that 😂 My life at the moment is a bit mad. I'm all over the place, travelling lots and working long hours whenever I am in the UK. This means I just have to do what I can. In the past this would have panicked me. I remember a few years ago I was really regimented with my training (and I respect anyone who is that way inclined); back then having a lack of routine would have stressed me out. Now, it's a different story. I don't put any pressure on myself. I roll with the punches and just do whatever is feasible. The key thing is that when I do train, I push myself hard so I can get a short and efficient workout squeezed in 🙌🏼💗

Chocolate peanut butter cups 😍 I was inspired by chocolate covered Katie (check out her blog) to make the cups 'inside out'! 1/2 cup peanut flour, 1/4 cup coconut oil, 4tsp maple syrup, 2 tbsp melted dark chocolate. Combine the pb, oil and syrup, but a thin layer in the bottle of cake cases and freeze for 5-10mins. Then do a layer of the melted chocolate, freeze. Finally add another layer of the peanut mix and freeze until set. These are super yummy treats, even my dad approves 👍

Glute Recovery 🍑 Everyone wants a peachy butt, myself included. But training your glutes repeatedly without supporting recovery is a recipe for disaster. You can develop muscular tightness and imbalances, and even injure yourself. I talk about this at length in my book (currently on sale for £5.99!) but for ease, here are three glute stretches you can add into your routine. These are great used post workout for 30 seconds minimum per stretch. Really focus on breathing into the muscle and consciously relaxing into the position. Try to gently and gradually move deeper into the stretch. Combine these with foam rolling and you're onto a winner 😘 Wearing @adidasuk 💕

Let's talk about self-love 💗 We often talk about loving our bodies, but what about loving our minds? 🙌🏼 I'm thankful to say that I've reached a place where I unconditionally love my body. However, and this is scary to say, I still have insecurities about who I am as a person 😳 Today at the @thegirlgains event we discussed our biggest self-perceived weaknesses and then were compassionate towards ourselves. I shared mine with the group and I want to share it with you too: I can be selfish. Why? I've had life experiences that have taught me to focus on myself and ignore what's happening around me. Which can be good in many ways - I'm happy to go in my own direction and against social norms - but also not so good. Sometimes it's important to be selfless, especially in friendships and relationships 👯 Today I realised this quality doesn't define me. It's just part of me, a result of my experiences and something I am working on every damn day to improve. I am on a constant journey of self-development. Most importantly; I love who I am right now, but I also love who I am becoming 💗

Ocean Plastic 🌊 Yesterday Ant and I found a stunning secluded beach. It was beautiful, but it was covered in plastic pollution 😢 We went back today and did a clear up; this was about half of what we found on only a couple of hundred metres of beach. We’re going back tomorrow to clean up more ☀️ Every year 8 million metric tonnes of plastic is dumped into the ocean. There are around 46,000 pieces of plastic per square mile of the ocean. Plastic doesn’t biodegrade so almost every single piece of plastic we have ever produced still exists in some form. This is destroying ecosystems and killing marine life 🐳 We NEED change, but what can we do? ➡️ Reuse any plastic products you have as much as possible rather than throwing them away. ➡️ Recycle recycle recycle. ➡️ Reduce. This is the big one. Recycling and reusing are great but ultimately we NEED to reduce how much plastic we use. Especially single use plastic such as straws, bottles and coffee cups. ➡️ Create wider change in your workplace. E.g. if you work at a cafe, ask if you can stop using straws or switch them for paper ones. ➡️ Clean up. If you do see ocean plastic please pick it up before it causes further harm. ➡️ Raise awareness. Talk to friends and family about this issue and ask them to watch documentaries such as “A Plastic Ocean” 🌊 I hope this post inspires you to make some small changes. If you want more support then please do join my private Facebook group: Living Consciously Crew where we share lots of tips and advice 🌎💗

A bit of a different transformation... My career! 🎓 I graduated two years ago today. I studied Speech Science at the University of Sheffield and came out with a first, I was over the moon! Yet here I am two years later, working in the fitness industry. I turned my back on what I had studied for years to become. I remember being terrified of disappointing my parents who wanted me to do a "proper job", a category fitness blogging didn't quite fit into 🙄 Instead of pursuing a career I didn't love, I took a gap year and told myself I had 12 months to make it happen. Giving myself that pressure made me work my little socks off. I trained as a PT and lived in an Air BnB on the outskirts of London until I found a flat share. I started personal training at @thelomaxway and built up a client base, all while developing my blog alongside it. My parents didn't quite get it and assumed I was just doing this for the summer, not for life. I remember the day I told them I was going to stick with it, they weren't sure it was the right move so I set out to prove to them it was! Now, two years after graduating, I LOVE my job and I think my parents are proud of me (at least I hope so!). I'm not saying everyone should abandon their degree after years of study, but I think it goes to show that it's ok to go against what is expected of you and you CAN achieve your goals when you work hard and never give up! 💕

Work Life Balance ✌🏼️Social media comparison isn't limited to body image. It can encompass your whole lifestyle. Right now it seems like everyone is working damn hard. People take pride in slogging away at their laptop at all hours of the day. It is admired to get hardly any sleep or work seven days a week. And if you don't work this hard? You're made to feel guilty. And you know what, I'm not about that life anymore. I've been there. I've done that. I've worked myself to burn out. I've had sleepless nights spent at my laptop. I've worked for weeks and weeks without a day off. It isn't fun and it isn't healthy. I'm a natural workaholic, I will drown myself in work if I can. But now, I still grind. I grind hard. But I pride myself on finally finding a work life balance. On finally giving myself time to relax. On finally being able to switch off from it all. And I don't feel guilty about it. So please don't make the mistakes I have in the past. Manage your stress levels. Take time out. Switch off. Disconnect. Look after yourself and look after your health😘 I talk about this at length in my book Strong, available to preorder at bit.ly/strongzvd 💕

Banana, chocolate and peanut protein fudge ☺ Blend in a food processor: 3 bananas, 2 heaping tbsp cocoa powder, 1 scoop chocolate protein powder, 1 tbsp honey, 1/2 cup + 2tbsp peanut flour, and 1 tsp vanilla extract. Pop in a foil lined pan and freeze for about 3 hours or until solid and then chop into pieces. Store in the freezer to avoid melting!

Dinner tonight = Moroccan Style Pork 🍴 For a single serving: Fry 1 small red onion in coconut oil until softened, add 150g lean pork mince and fry until browned. Add 1 chopped garlic clove, half a tsp of curry paste, the zest of half a lemon, a tbsp of tomato purée and cook for 2 mins. Add 1/3 can of chopped tomatoes, half a red bell pepper and a glug of water. Cover and simmer on a low heat for 20 minutes. I served mine on a bed of little gem lettuce leaves ☺️

HEALTHY PECAN PIE!!! 😍 Nope, your eyes are not deceiving you! This pecan pie is: all natural, raw, vegan, and gluten free! First, get a loose bottomed cake tin and line it with baking paper. Then get a food processor and combine 200g pitted dates, 1/2 cup cashews, 1/2 cup almonds, 1/2 tsp cinnamon and 1/4 cup unsweetened almond milk. Blend blend blend until it forms a sticky paste. Push the mixture into the bottom of the cake tin to form the crust. Now for the filling. Pop in a food processor: 1 cup pecans, 1 tub (170g) cashew butter, 200g dates and 3/4 cup unsweetened almond milk. Blend blend blend until it forms a smooth thick creamy paste. Pour this over the base and level it out. Finish the pie off by decorating the top with some more pecans. Pop it in the fridge to set for 1 hour, then take it out and remove it from the tin before you devour it! It tastes incredible and can last around 5 days when stored in the fridge! 😊You can find more recipes like this in my ebooks linked on my profile! Cacao Cranberry Vegan Blondies 😍 Want to treat your loved ones this mother’s day? Or just treat yourself? 😝 Whip up these cacao and cranberry blondies using @bluediamonduk's amazing new Nutri + range 🙌🏼 Here’s how : blend 1 can of drained & rinsed chickpeas with 1 cup @bluediamonduk Almond Breeze Nutri +Fibre. Add to a bowl and then stir in: 1 tsp baking powder, 1 cup melted peanut butter, 1 tsp vanilla extract, 1/2 cup maple syrup, 1/2 cup ground almonds, 1/2 cup cranberries and 1/2 cup cacao nibs (or chocolate chips!). Combine until smooth then pour into a greased baking tray. Bake in a preheated oven at 200 degrees for 30 minutes. Then leave to cool before slicing up and enjoying! 💕

My transformation ✌🏼️ Change doesn't have to be dramatic and progress doesn't have to mean weight loss ☺️ Left to right: 1️⃣ 62kg. Eating anything and everything. Regular boozing. Zero training. Fad diets when I fancied them. "Skinny fat" with no strength or muscle tone. 2️⃣ 67kg. Getting into health and fitness. I had been lifting for about a year and was still experimenting with healthy eating. Wasn't totally balanced - went through phases of clean eating, paleo and IIFYM as I tried to find my groove. Gained weight in the form of muscle. 3️⃣ 71kg. Four years after the first photo. I have been lifting weights consistently for over three years. I also enjoy HIIT classes like @f45londonbridge. I'm definitely the physically fittest I've ever been. I've finally found my groove with nutrition and am able to eat intuitively for my bodies needs. I'm super balanced and eat pretty much everything. Moderation not deprivation is my motto! 😝 Bear in mind that I am not flexing in these photos. If you go into my feed you can see the muscle mass I have gained (I say this as I'm getting a lot of comments saying there isn't a difference). 🙈 I know I don't look massively different between these photos but the mental and physical change is huge. I have gained almost 10kg and I am so much stronger & fitter than I was when I started. The most important change though? I'm healthy and happy in myself. I train and eat well because I love my body and I celebrate everything it can do 💕

STOP, DROP and STRETCH! 👊🏼 I'm gonna bet that you have tight hip flexors. It's extremely common in our modern lives where we spent much of our time sat at desks. This can lead to muscular imbalances, and further down the line even injuries. So to combat this, here is a hip flexor stretch with two progressions1️⃣ Basic hip flexor stretch 2️⃣ Arm raised to extend the stretch up through your core 3️⃣ Back leg lifted to extend the stretch through your quads 👌🏼 Keep your core engaged and squeeze the glute of the rear leg, imagine you're tucking it under your core. You should REALLY feel it down the front of that leg. Hold for 30+ seconds to feel the best benefits 🙌🏼 Wearing @adidaswomen at @fitnessfirstuk 💕

1/4 REP LADDERS 😷 These are vile. They literally destroy your legs! I put @thefoodmedic through them today and she agreed! 👯 My strength coach @awillis1515 has programmed them for me and I simultaneously dread them and love them every time 😅 Basically on Bulgarian split squats you do: on rep one you do a full rep, then rep two you do one 1/4 rep pulse at the bottom, the next rep you do 3 1/4 rep pulses and the next you do 4 1/4 rep pulses and continue this up to 8 or 10 reps. Then switch leg and repeat. The burn is insane! 🔥 Adam puts this in my program at the end of sessions to fatigue my muscles. The 1/4 reps themselves give more time under tension at the hardest part of the movement 👊🏼 (This video is slightly sped up) 💪🏼 Let me know how you get on with these! 😘 Wearing @asicseurope kicks, @teameverysecond leggings and an @activeinstyle top 💕

Carbs DO NOT make you fat 😤 I haven't tracked my macros in about 18 months. This week I have been tracking them out of interest - to check how much protein/fats/carbs I get in my predominantly plant based diet. I won't share my exact macros but I will say I eat A LOT of carbs. Over 250g a day. And less protein than you might expect. Under 100g a day. And you know what? I'm getting leaner. I'm getting stronger. I'm getting more powerful in the gym. I'm feeling super energised and I'm hitting PBs. I feel like I'm fitter than ever. I remember a few years ago I used to be so scared of carbs, keeping them as low as possible. Now I am thriving on them! 💪🏼 I am not saying everyone should go stuffing their faces with carbs. Different protocols work for different people, and it all has to be put into the unique context of your lifestyle, preferences and so much more. But I just want to reassure you that carbs do not make you fat. I'm basically a human carb and I'm not fat 😂 Please. Don't fear food. Use it as fuel for your amazing body 💗 Wearing @adidasuk at @un1t_fulham 🙌🏼

I know most of you guys follow me for my recipes, but I've recently been getting a lot of emails asking about my training ☺️ I train with @naomilbailey and we have an upper/lower/HIIT/rest training split, and then we repeat. I used to split workouts into specific body parts but on the recommendation of @brynray I changed to upper/lower. This works for me as it means each body part gets trained twice a week 👍 I prefer HIIT cardio over LISS as it's more challenging and helps boost your metabolism! We lift as heavy as we can while maintaining form and aim for between 8-12 reps depending on the exercise. Sometimes we chuck in 5x5 training to change it up. Our training sessions are maximum an hour and we have short rest periods to keep the intensity up. I will post some of our workouts in the future 💪

Let's talk about getting healthy 💁🏼 I get SO many questions every day from you guys about various aspects of training and nutrition - usually the tiny details. I find that people get so caught up in the little things like what time they train or the frequency of their meals, when in reality these don't matter for 90% of people. What matters is that you train on a regular basis, enjoy yourself and push yourself in your workouts. What matters is that it fits into your schedule, whether that's early in the morning or late at night is irrelevant. In terms of diet - focus on eating wholesome single-ingredient foods as much as you can and getting in enough protein to support your training. There's no need to obsess about how many meals you have or whether you should eat asparagus or broccoli for dinner. What really matters is that you're fuelling your body and making consistent healthy choices. There's no magic secret to getting healthy. Detox teas and juice cleanses are bullshit. It's about making sustainable changes over time and making these into habits. So don't sweat the small stuff and focus on making healthy choices on a daily basis 🙏🏼🙌🏼

2 years of (shoulder) gains 💪😂 Just went on a trip down memory lane and scrolled back to the start of my Instagram. I came across the picture on the left! It was taken when I had just started to lift weights. At this point I had never used a proper barbell and I was scared of going into the "man area" of the gym. If I could go back and give myself two pieces of advice I would say: 1) Suck it up and go lift with the big boys. They won't judge you, they'll respect you. 2) Push yourself harder. Doing lunges with the same 5kg weights for 6 months isn't going to get you very far 🙈 And my one piece of advice for you is: weights don't make you bulky. They don't make you manly. They help you to sculpt your body. Give them a go and once you start seeing the results, you won't regret it! ☺️💕

Single Serving Chocolate Cookie 🍪 I got a cookie craving while revising this afternoon so whipped this up. The recipe isn't perfect and I'll have to tweak it but it's not bad for 4 ingredients 😜 Preheat the oven to 180c and grease a piece of tin foil and pop it on a tray. Mix together 1 egg white, 1 tbsp cocoa powder and 2 tbsp almond flour. Once combined add half a tsp of natural flavouring or extracts - I added orange extract. Taste the batter and add a tsp of honey if it's not sweet enough for you, but I like it as it is. Pour the batter onto the tinfoil and bake for 5-10mins until cooked through. Take it out the oven, smother it in peanut butter and devour it 👌

Ok guys. For real. This superset is going to burn your legs more than ever before 🔥 A little pre-warning. Please don't do this unless you're comfortable with Bulgarian split squats. A lot of people nowadays have very tight hip flexors which make this movement particularly challenging. Check your form with a professional first 👊🏼 Alrighty here it is: ➡️ Bulgarian split squats x 10 on one leg ➡️ Drop the weight and go straight into 10 plyometric split squats on that same leg 😷 Then repeat on the other leg! 💪🏼 I recommend doing these near the beginning of a workout while you still have a good amount of energy in the tank! 😝 Wearing @adidasuk at @fitnessfirstuk 💕
