Full body sculpting 💪🏼 I was just playing around with the equipment at @thelomaxway and came up with this exercise. It's amazing for your legs (especially your glutes 🍑), core and shoulders! Do a slow controlled twisting mountain climber with your hands on the ball. Then place your foot by the ball, sit up into a lunge pushing through your heel and press the ball over head. Return to the plank and repeat. This is a great addition to full body workouts or a nice way to exhaust your core and legs at the end of a tough lower body workout 👌🏻I love coming up with new moves for my clients ☺️ If you want me to train you - drop me an email: zannavandijk@gmail.com 😘 Top = @activeinstyle and leggings = @heyjolondon 💕 Thanks @adamstansbury for filming 🙏🏻

🍪 Protein Flapjack 🍪 This recipe is super simple and customisable. Just mix together 1 and 1/2 cup oats, with 1/2 cup unsweetened almond milk, 1/2 cup nut butter and 2-3 scoops of whey protein (I recommend @team_optimum). Combine thoroughly, pour into a tray, pop into the fridge or freezer to set, and then chop up into slices👌 You can use whatever variety of nut butter and flavour of protein, such as the classic peanut butter with chocolate whey 💁 You can use the code ROSVD10 to get 10% off @team_optimum products and you can find more recipes like this in my eBook which is linked on my profile 😘

So you want to do a chin up? 💪🏼 Here are some exercises you can do to build strength to do the real deal 😚 Note: my head is moving because there's a bar above the pull up bar I had to avoid & this video is sped up 1.5x) 👌🏼 Here we go: 1️⃣ Regular chin ups (to show form) 2️⃣ Eccentric chin ups (jump up and lower down super slowly!) 3️⃣ Chin-up holds - hold yourself in a mid chin up position. Stay here as long as possible. 4️⃣ Banded chin ups - pop your knee or foot in a band and do chin ups as normal to failure ✌🏼️ When I was building up to doing pull ups I was doing this sort of training 2 times a week as well as other back and arm training. Now I just do chin ups as part of my back training once a week. Let me know how you get on with these exercises! 😘 Outfit is @activeinstyle @adanola and this is filmed at @equinox 💁🏼 Shoutout to @lbp_adamwillis for showing me these moves 💕

When someone asks me what I value the most, they expect me to say my car or my laptop, but I always say my memories. I have been lucky enough to travel the world throughout my childhood and teenage years, as well as backpack through Asia more recently. These trips have taught me so much, and the experiences I have had on them have been life changing. I will never forget some of the incredible moments I have experienced. I would happily sacrifice objects for these memories. The experiences you value don't have to be from travel, they can be anything. A day at the park, as trip to the seaside. But consciously reflect on these, realise how amazing they are. Write them down, scrapbook about them, do something. Don't lose them. ✌🏻️

Plane Supplies ✈️ I'm about to hop on a plane to THE MALDIVES. No biggie 😱 And I wanted to share my carry on essentials 🙌🏼➡️ My passport - obviously 😂 ➡️ Snacks - you never know what airplane food is going to be like. So I always take my own snacks. Today I've got a stash of @aldiuk wholefood bars - I'm obsessed with the cashew crush and pecan pie flavours. Plus they only have TWO ingredients! 🙌🏼 I'm not one of those people who refuses to eat plane food, but I do request a vegan meal as it tends to be more wholesome. ➡️ A reusable water bottle. You can easily go through 10 plastic cups or mini bottles on a long haul flight. To avoid this excessive trash, take your own bottle and ask the air hostess to refill it for you! 💦🌎 ➡️ A skincare regimen - I am pretty anal about how I look after my skin on flights. If you want a post or video about this let me know! ➡️ Entertainment. I always take my laptop as I'm most productive on flights. 🌟 4 Ingredient Protein Peanut Butter Biscuits 🌟 You need: 1 cup peanut butter, 1 scoop protein powder (I used chocolate), 1 egg, 1 tsp vanilla. Mix the ingredients thoroughly - it is easier if you slightly warm the PB so it's more mixable. I also added a tsp of almond milk to help the ingredients combine. Then pop the mixture on a baking sheet in biscuit shapes and bake for about 10-12 minutes at 180. Take them out the oven and let them cool and set for 10 minutes... Then gobble them up 😂👌

Raspberry Dark Chocolate Brownies 😍 Here's another recipe that @salboi and I created together! Chuck in a food processor: 1 can chickpeas (drained, rinsed and dried), 1 cup soft dates, 100g dark melted chocolate (85%+), 1/2 cup peanut butter, 1/4 cup cocoa powder, 1/3 cup honey, 1/2 cup almond milk, 1 tsp vanilla and 1 tsp baking powder. Once combed pour the mixture into a bowl and stir through 1/3 cup white chocolate chips and 1 cup raspberries. You can omit the white chocolate chips if you want but they're amazing! Then just pour the batter into a lined tray and bake at 180c/350f for 30-40 mins. Leave to cool and set, chop up and dig in! 💁 More recipes like this can be found in my ebooks - the link to them is on my profile 💕

Sheffield, it’s been a pleasure 🙌🏼 Let’s talk about my career 🎓 If you guys don’t know, I studied Speech and Language Therapy at the University of Sheffield for four years. (And I got a first, woohoo!) 🎉 I often get asked if I regret spending four years studying a field I didn’t end up working in 🤔 My answer? Not at all! University shaped who I am and without those experiences I wouldn’t be here today. I am not naturally gifted when it comes to studying and I had to graft damn hard to get the results I wanted. Uni taught me how to structure my time and developed my work ethic. I also not only learnt how to analyse scientific evidence and write academically, but I found fitness as an escape during my time studying. Ultimately, it ended up leading me to the passion which I pursue today. Plus I got to meet some damn good eggs like @naomilbailey 👯 Realistically, I work in a fragile and unpredictable field. Blogging is new and no one quite knows where it’s going and the longevity of the industry. No matter how much I try and build a solid brand, I know it could all collapse around me at a moments notice. Pretty scary hey 😜 So it’s reassuring to have a degree behind me to fall back on if need be in the future 🙌🏼 Plus, who doesn’t like calling themselves a Bachelor of Medical Science!? 🤓💗

Bank holiday workout done ✅ I just want to let you guys know that not all my workouts are amazing! Of course I post the most fun and challenging sessions on here, as I want to motivate you and provide some workout inspiration 🙌🏼 However, I do have those days where I just can't be bothered. The ones where I'm just not feeling it. And that is TOTALLY ok. It's human. It's life. Most of the time when I get in a funk, I just focus on getting myself to the gym. Once I get there and start my workout I usually warm up to the idea and end up having a good one. That being said, some days I'm just not in the zone. I get to the gym, I do a few sets and my body & mind are like NOPE I don't wanna do this. Some days I wake up to my 5am alarm and I can feel that my body just needs rest so I go straight back to sleep. I never judge myself harshly for these decisions. It's listening to my body and it's often just me looking after myself 🙌🏼 Not every single workout is doing to be epic. Some are great. Some are average. Some are shite. What matters is that we consistently move our bodies and that we have more good workouts than poor ones 💪🏼 Wearing @adidasuk 💗

Snickers Protein Bars 😍 This recipe is taken from my second ebook - the link to it is on my profile! Mix together 1 cup runny peanut butter, 3 scoops @team_optimum vanilla whey (the code ROSVD10 gets 10% off), 2 cups oats and 1/2 cup unsweetened almond milk. Press this into the bottom of a small tray. Spread a thin layer of peanut butter over this and freeze until set (about 30mins). Melt 100g 85%+ dark chocolate and pour this over the top of the peanut butter. Spread to make a thin layer. Freeze again until set (about 30 mins). Chop up into bars and store in the fridge. White Chocolate and Pecan Blondies 😍 @salboi and I did some experimental baking last night and this was the result. Guys, these are seriously the BEST thing I have ever baked. They are insanely good! The only naughty ingredient is the white chocolate chips which you can omit if you want 👍 In a food processor combine: 1 can chickpeas (drained rinsed and dried - 240g), 1/2 cup soft dates, 1/4 cup honey, 1 tsp baking powder, 1 tsp vanilla essence, 1 cup natural peanut butter, and 3/4 cup unsweetened almond milk. Pour this mixture into a mixing bowl and stir in 1/2 cup white chocolate chips (optional but amazing) and 1/3 cup chopped pecans. Grease a baking tray and chuck in the mixture. Sprinkle 1/3 cup pecans on top of blondies.
Bake in a 180c fan oven for 20-25 mins. Leave to cool and set! 👌 More recipes like this can be found in the ebook linked on my profile! If you make this recipe be sure to tag me @blondehealth and

Ok, let's talk 💁🏼 Today a girl came up and asked me "So, if you're a fitness blogger; do you eat like no carbs?". I'm sorry, what?! Guys these are the comments that worry me! There are so many distorted perceptions of what healthy is. I consider myself to be a healthy person. I eat carbs multiple times a day, including the evening. I eat gluten. I eat dairy. I eat bread. I eat chocolate. I eat doughnuts. I'm partial to a cheeky cocktail. I don't always drink 2 litres of water. I don't eat a ridiculous amount of protein. I'm not a big fan of salads. I don't weigh and measure every gram of food that passes my lips. I go out to eat multiple times a week. Sometimes I eat too much and sometimes I eat too little. I don't train everyday. My workouts are short and sweet. I don't do hours of cardio. I lift weights. All in all, I have a balanced approach to food, fitness and LIFE! I love my body and I look after it by training hard and nourishing it with wholesome foods 80% of the time. However I will never deprive myself of enjoying a social meal with my bestie or sharing a tub of ice cream with my boyfriend. Being healthy isn't about restriction, it's about living a sustainable, enjoyable and balanced lifestyle 👌🏼💕

My Current Favourite Leg Exercise 🔥 I've had a lot of clients struggle with traditional Bulgarian split squats where your back foot is on a bench or step. Often their range of motion is compromised due to tightness/imbalances. This means that they can't perform the exercise effectively and often feel it more in their quads and have little/no glute activation going on 😫So, I find that using a TRX allows them to go all the way down into the movement and really engage their hammies and glutes as well as their quads 💪🏼 I personally love adding on TRX split squats at the end of a workout using the second variation in this video - 1 & 1/2 reps. This movement, with a focus on stabilising my knee and pushing through my heels, really burns out my booty 😝 Give it a go! 🙌🏼 Wearing @adidasuk 💗

🌟Protein Brownies🌟 You need: 1 can of drained rinsed and dried chick peas, 1/4 cup cocoa powder, 2 scoops chocolate protein powder, 1/4 cup honey, 1/2 cup peanut butter, 1 tsp baking powder, 1/4 cup unsweetened almond milk, 1 egg white. Just pop all the ingredients in a blender and whizz it up until the mixture is smooth. Then pour this into a lined baking tray and bake at 180 for around 15 minutes 👍

Tight traps? Try this 🙌🏼 I suffer from ridiculously CRAZYYY tight traps. It's mad. They're like rocks 😂 And this is the one thing (along with regular sports massages) which releases them 👌🏼 Place a trigger point ball (you can order one off amazon) between your traps and a wall. This works best in a crawling position. Then push towards the wall, putting pressure through the ball and into your trap. This is gonna hurt. A lot. Breathe through it and try desperately to relax your traps to ease the tension. Then move to another tight spot and repeat. Ooooooosh. You'll feel this the next day!!! 😝 Thanks for showing me this tip @mikeleept 🤓 Wearing @Adidasuk 💗

Expectation VS Reality 🙌🏼 I'm not a huge fan of these comparison photos but I think this is a really important message to share. I could have just posted the photo on the left, where my cellulite is edited out, and you would have thought that my body looked like that. Reality check. It doesn't. I'm the same as you. I have cellulite. I'm covered in the stuff (thanks for the genes mum!). Oh and not forgetting my abundance of stretch marks. I've got it all 💁🏼 But you know what? I genuinely do not care. I don't even think about it! Let alone worry about it. Why? Because it's natural. It's part of being a woman. Most of us have it, and we have been conditioned to be ashamed of it. Who said it's a bad thing?! Who dictated that fact? No one. It's something we have learnt. A lie we tell ourselves. And I refuse to believe it. Instead I embrace my body with all it's so called "flaws" because it's mine. It is my vehicle through life and I love it for all it does for me. Having cellulite does not define me, it is part of me and for that I am grateful 💗

Shoulder Burner 🔥 Here is a snippet from today's upper body workout (see the full thing on my Instagram story!) 💪🏼 This is a mechanical drop set, a technique @shaunstafford showed me. Basically, complete a set of dumbbell shoulder presses, then drop the bench a notch and complete another set; then take the bench down another notch and do a final set. This means one full set is made up of 3 sets at different inclines. Back to back. With the same weight. Ouch! 😷 Then rest, and repeat 2-3 more times. Go lighter than you think as your arms will turn to jelly 😝 Good luck 🙌🏼 Wearing @adidasuk at @easygym 💗

Lets talk about the MARATHON 🏃 So yesterday my beautiful friends @twicethehealth offered me a place in London Marathon. My initial reaction was YES. What an opportunity. I should totally take it! 🎉 However I then sat down and really thought about it. My heart said yes, but my head said no. Endurance sport is amazing and I hugely admire those who run marathons. I do want to run one some day. But it's not something to be taken lightly. Often people throw themselves into marathons without really thinking about it. In reality it's a huge deal. You NEED to be savvy. See a physio before you start training. Get a gait analysis. Work around any imbalances. Get regular check ups as you go along. Have a coach and a proper training program. And dedicate hours every week to your runs 💦 It's a huge commitment, and with my absolutely manic schedule over the coming months I just don't think I would be able to do it safely. If I'm going to do a marathon, I'm going to do it right. And this year I cant do that. My body, performance and health are too precious to me to risk it 😅 So the takeaway message is this: endurance sport is INCREDIBLE but please think long and hard before throwing yourself in at the deep end. You need to be able to commit to it wholeheartedly to avoid injury and to enjoy the journey. And if you do take part? Breakfast this morning was a bowl of raw "cookie dough" 👍 It's actually made from chickpeas... I know I know, it sounds about as appealing as a camels arse. However, it actually tastes amazing! Healthy Chocolate Chip Cookie Dough Bites 🙊 This is a very popular recipe here on Instagram and I've seen a lot of variations of it... This is the version that I've found works best for me! It makes the most delicious melt-in-your-mouth cookie dough bites 👌 Pop in a blender: 1 can of drained rinsed and dried chickpeas, 1/2 cup peanut butter, 1/4 cup honey, 1 tsp baking powder, and 1 tsp vanilla extract. Blend this up until it's smooth and creamy. Then stir in a handful of dark chocolate chips. Grab a spoon and pop little mounds of the mixture on a lined baking tray - whatever size you want depending on if you want bites or full on cookies! Then bake at 180 for around 10 minutes. They're still soft when they come out the oven so leave them to cool (and eat one a sneaky warm one 🙊) and then enjoy 👍

Melt In The Middle Chocolate Peanut Butter Protein Cupcakes 😍 Combine 1/2 cup chocolate @team_optimum protein powder (use the code ROSVD10 for 10% off!), 1/2 cup flour (I recommend oat flour or brown rice flour), 1/4 cup cocoa powder, 1 tsp baking powder, 170g Greek yoghurt, 1 egg, 1 egg white, 1/3 cup powdered stevia and 1/4 cup almond milk. Divide the mixture between 9 cupcake cases. Pop half a tablespoon of peanut butter in each case and push it down so it's submerged in the batter. Bake in a preheated 180c oven for 10-15 minutes until cooked through. They're best eaten fresh from the oven or you can reheat them later to remelt the centre 😍 This recipe along with loads more can be found in my ebooks, the link to them is on my profile! 💕

Brownies smothered in melted peanut butter and dark chocolate chips 😍 The recipe is back in my feed but I'll repost: Preheat oven to 180 degrees. In a blender combine: 170g Greek yoghurt, 1/4 cup almond milk, 1 large egg, 1 tsp baking powder, 1/2 cup powdered sweetener (I use stevia), 1/2 cup cocoa powder and 1/2 cup oats. Pour the mixture into a small lined baking tin. Microwave 1/2 cup peanut butter until melted. Use a spoon to drizzle and pour it over the brownie mixture. Then sprinkle with dark chocolate chips, and pop in the oven for around 20 minutes 👌

Day One vs Now ⏱ The photo on the left was taken 7 years ago, before I had ever set foot in a gym. I lived on a diet of pizza, vodka and shortbread biscuits and I don’t regret it at all. I needed to get it out of my system 😂 Since then my journey has been up and down. Along the way I’ve made so many mistakes. So. Many. Mistakes 😅 I fell into fad diets and excessive training in the early days, because that’s what I thought constituted “fitness” 🙈 Eventually, through years of trial and error, I found my own balance, one which truly makes me happy. I have a flexible fitness routine combining body weight training, weights and running. No macros. No calorie counting. No weighing myself or my meals. I eat plant based whole foods and I’m basically a human carb 🍞 For me, the goal is long term health and happiness, so I focus on enjoying my training and nutrition. No extreme restrictions. Just conscious eating and regular movement. 💃🏼 So what’s the lesson? It’s a journey. Embrace the highs and lows, as they shape who you are. Avoid fads. Think long term. Prioritise health. Be gentle with yourself. And most importantly never compare your chapter 1 to someone else’s chapter 20 📚

"Zanna, do you eat carbs? Do you eat gluten? What about pasta and bread?" YES! I eat everything. For me what works is a balanced diet where I allow myself all foods in moderation. I personally run best on fairly high carbohydrates so a large portion of my daily food intake comes from rice, sweet potato, fruit etc. I have a high protein intake and moderate fat intake. I also don't respond badly to gluten, pasta or bread so I will eat these on occasion. I am not intolerant to them so I don't need to cut them out. However obviously they are processed so I try to choose whole food carbohydrates first. (However, I do eat chocolate almost every day 🙊). These food choices are what works for ME! Please don't look at what I do and think that is the right way or only way to eat. It is just my way. I don't recommend my clients eat the same as me, I tailor my advice to their goals, preferences, training regimes, etc. There is no one diet plan that will give everyone results. I've been through years of trial and error and only recently with @alexjamesritson's guidance have I found exactly what works for me 😊 Meal: from @freshfitnessfood, code ZANNA10 gets 10% off 💕

Blueberry Banana Bread 🍌 Combine: 3 cups almond flour (you can substitute this for oat flour), 3-4 overly ripe mashed bananas, 1 tsp baking powder, 1 tsp vanilla extract, 1/2 tsp cinnamon, 2 eggs, and 2 tbsp Greek yoghurt. Once thoroughly mixed, gently stir in 2/3 cup of blueberries. Pour into a lined loaf tin and bake at 180c/350f for around 30-45 mins. The bread is cooked when a toothpick comes out clean 👌

Ab Circuit 🔥 Try adding in this circuit at the end of your workouts to burn out your core! Just do each exercise for 30 seconds back to back. Rest 30 seconds after each round. Repeat three times. Ouch 😷 ➡️ Plank Hip Dips - don't let your hips raise up into the air! Keep them low and twist through your obliques ➡️ Hollow Body Hold - consciously press your lower back into the ground, brace your core and tuck your chin into your chest ➡️ Bicycle Crunches - lift the opposite shoulder off the ground as you take it towards the knee. Again focus on pushing the lower back into the floor 💪🏼 Please note that the first and last exercise are sped up. Wearing @adidasuk 💗

So here I am, one month into my backpacking adventure! In terms of diet I have to admit I've eaten pretty badly for most of the trip so far 🙊 I want to try all the local food and it isn't always the healthiest option! However, I'm not worried. I would rather wholeheartedly embrace the travelling experience and local culture than restrict myself for the sake of being lean! I have plenty of time when I'm home to get back on track. In terms of fitness, I have been training 3-4 times a week. I am using resistance bands, cables and my backpack as weights 💪 I am also being very active here, with regular trekking and cycling trips 👍 For more pictures of my adventures check out my @zanzapan account 💕

Full Body Gym Workout 💪🏼 Today I headed to Hammerhead Gym in Seminyak, Bali to smash out a weights session. As I'm not lifting regularly when I travel, lots of my sessions are full body. Today I focused on heavy compound lifts. I did 1️⃣ Squats 2️⃣ Push Press 3️⃣ Sumo Deadlifts 4️⃣ Pull ups 👊🏼 For the squats, push press and deadlifts I did 5 sets getting progressively heavier weights and lower reps with each set. I worked up to about 5-6 reps. For pull ups I did 5 sets to failure which for me was 5, 4, 4, 3 and 3 reps 👌🏼 By the end of the session I was destroyed and ready to eat a food mountain! 😂 My top travel tip is, when you do get access to a gym, be efficient and do full body workouts to make the most of your time! 💕

5 Minute Abs 🔥 Try this cheeky superset to develop your core strength. I personally find hollow body hold variations really effective for challenging my core so I often use this combination: 1️⃣ A 30 second hollow body hold. Key points: lower back consciously pushed into the ground, shoulder blades off the floor. Make it harder by lowering the legs towards the floor 2️⃣ Leg Drop & Crunch x 20 (10 each leg). As you drop each leg, again consciously keep the lower back pushed into the floor. When you crunch up, lift those shoulder blades. Take your time, no rushing 💪🏼 For me, training my core can't be done absent mindedly or in a rush. I really need to focus on engaging the correct muscles otherwise my body just gets lazy. Be conscious in your movements and feel the burn 😝 I repeat this superset 3 times through 🙌🏼 Wearing @adidasuk at @easygym 💗

Leg Finisher 💀 I demolished my legs today by adding in this sweaty superset at the end of my workout. I waddled home like a penguin 🐧😂 I did ➡️ Leg extension drop set. Complete 10 reps on a heavy weight, squeezing your quads at the top. Then immediately half the weight and complete 10 more reps. ➡️ Hop off the machine and do 15 squat jumps 🔥🔥🔥 Repeat 3 times. Your legs will be on FIYYYAAHHHH 😝 I am actually putting more focus on my quads at the moment as they are disproportionally weak compared to my hammies & glutes 🍑 To avoid injury and to improve my overall athletic performance, I am trying to balance out my body 💪🏼 Wearing @adidasuk at @easygym 💗

⭐Lean turkey burgers ⭐ My mum bought some lean turkey mince today and asked me to show her how to make something with it, these are the end result: 500g extra lean turkey mince, 4 diced spring onions, finely diced thumb size piece of ginger, 1 small egg, 1 tablespoon of chopped parsley, salt and pepper.

Mix the ingredients and make into burgers (this mixture makes 6-7) . Chill for 10-15 mins. You can then fry them in coconut oil for 4-5mins each side or grill them for 7-8 mins each side.

Nutella brownies 😍 I literally threw some ingredients together, hoped for the best, and ended up making the best brownies EVER! I might have eaten 2... or 3 🙊 You need: 1 cup flour (I used almond but think brown rice or oat flour would work too), 1/3 cup honey, 1/3 cup cocoa powder, 1/2 cup dark chocolate hazelnut butter (mines from the protein works), 1 egg, 2 tbsp melted grass fed butter (or coconut oil would work), 1/2 tsp baking powder, and 1 tsp vanilla. Just mix the ingredients, pour into a lined tray and bake at 180 for about 20 minutes. When you take them out they're super fudgey and soft, so let them cool for about 15 minutes before you slice them! Then try not to eat them all at once 😂👌

Christmas spiced dark chocolate and almond protein truffles 😍 1/2 cup almond butter, 1/2 tsp cinnamon, 1/2 tsp ginger, a pinch of ground cloves, 2/3 cup vanilla protein powder (I used @myprotein), 50g of dark chocolate (I used 90% lindt), a couple of tablespoons of almond milk. Combine everything except the milk and chocolate. Slowly add the milk until the dough is moist and mouldable. Shape it into balls and refrigerate for 15 mins. Then melt the dark chocolate, coat the truffles and refrigerate again for half an hour 👍 Sorry to spam your feed with recipes guys... I had a baking day today!

Try adding this move to your leg/glute workouts 🍑 It's a single leg squat to a box/bench and it's MUCH harder than it looks - it is a killer for your quads, hammies and glutes. I use a bench because I'm 6 foot 2, but it would be too high for a lot of people - for those of you who are shorter than me (99% of the you 😂) I recommend using a lower box. Just sit down on it, lift one leg off the floor and stand up using the other leg alone. Lower yourself back to the bench with control. D I S C O N N E C T ✌🏼 Recently I found myself struggling to think clearly. My mind was so clouded with information. I was constantly flooding my brain with stimulus. Even in moments where I intended to relax, I would watch Ted talks or listen to educational podcasts. Constantly on a mission to learn 📚 I soon realised this was doing little for me. Don't get me wrong, I value learning highly. It's an amazing thing. But it's not productive if you don't give yourself to head space to think. To reflect. To absorb 💭 Since realising this, I've taken a step back and consciously switched off multiple times a day. In those moments I would plug in, I disconnect. Instead of watching Ted talks as I get ready in the morning, I do so in silence. Instead of plugging in a podcast on a walk, I walk in silence. Instead of doing emails on the bus, I sit in silence. Honestly, the change has been HUGE. I've had so much space to think. As a result I'm more driven and less stressed. I feel less connected to the outside world, but more connected to myself. Which is the most powerful and valuable connection to have 💗

Self-love 💗 I've just shared my personal journey to self-love over on @thegirlgains Instagram ☺️ The first message I received was "well of course you love yourself". That made my heart sink. Why is one persons journey to self-love more valid that anyone else's? Surely, the more body positivity we share online the better 🙌🏼 One of the biggest challenges I've faced when learning to love myself is other people's opinions. I've often felt ashamed to talk about my past struggles with my body. I felt like my story wasn't valid because I've never been overweight or had an eating disorder. I haven't been to any extremes, but I still spent an awfully long time disliking my body. Well, I want to share a message for any traditionally "slim" girls out there. It's assumed that you must love your body. That you can't ever feel low or self-critical. No, that's not the case. I'm here to tell you that your feelings towards yourself are perfectly valid no matter what your shape. Everyone has the right to go on their own journey to self love. So please don't be ashamed to share your experiences or your feelings no matter that your body type. You never know who you're helping or inspiring 💗🙌🏼

Recently I've been asked "WHY?" 🤔 Why are you taking up gymnastics? Why are you posting videos of handstands? Why? Let me tell you. To me, it's about challenging yourself. It is so easy to get comfortable. Especially with your training. You get into a routine. You enjoy it. You don't switch it up. Then you stagnate. I strongly believe that great things never come from comfort zones. It's important to learn to be comfortable with being uncomfortable. I have taken up gymnastics with @mikeleept because it's not something I'm naturally good at. I'm tall. I'm lanky. I'm uncoordinated. Gymnastics and me, we are certainly not a match made in heaven. And that's exactly why I'm pushing myself to do it. Because it's damn hard. It's teaching me so much about myself and my body. And I love that 🙌🏼 Guys, fitness doesn't have to be going to the gym and lifting weights. Heading outside for a run. Taking a yoga class. You can define your own version of fitness. Find something you enjoy and make it your own 💕

👆3 years ago at 62kg 👆1 year ago at 70kg 👆1 month ago at 72kg 😊 Some people may see this image and think I've made no progress at all. I see it and I'm amazed by how far I have come 💁On the left I was a cardio queen with a restrictive diet. In the middle I was lifting weights and getting to grips with nutrition. Now on the right I lift heavy, do minimal cardio, eat like a horse and have a healthy relationship with food. I have been lifting weights consistently for about 2 years now. I lift as heavy as I can. I've gained 10kg of weight. Nope I'm not bulky. Nope I'm not manly. I want to show that the scales can be deceiving when you lift 💪 My goals recently have been performance based - doing bodyweight pull ups and lifting a 100kg deadlift. While focussing on these (both of which I have now achieved!) I have made the most progress both mentally and physically. I am fitter and stronger than ever before and my nutrition is balanced, flexible and sustainable. Instead of focussing on abs and thigh gaps, I focus on strength, power and feeling good. Right now I can honestly say that although I'm not super lean with a rippling six pack, I love my body more than ever before and I'm proud of everything that it can do 🙏🙌 A big thank you to my coaches @alexjamesritson and @awillis1515 for helping me achieve balance 💕

Cable Tricep Exercises 🔥 Everyone else is tryna grow a booty and I'm over here making arm gains 😂💪🏼Girls - training lower body is awesome and i know we all want a peachy tush. But please don't neglect your upper body! I recommend targeting it with compound movements like pull ups, barbell presses and rows. Then once you're fatiguing, throw in some isolation exercises like those in this video. Here we have ➡️ Cable tricep push downs ➡️ 1 and 1/2 cable tricep push downs ➡️ Overhead tricep extensions ➡️ Single arm cable kickbacks 😝 Choose a weight that challenges you and go for 3 sets of 10-12 reps. Dumbbell Only Full Body Workout 💪🏼 Perfect for when you're in a limited hotel gym! Only got a pair of dumbbells to hand? Today was tough 💀 It’s time for some honesty guys. I haven’t put fitness at the top of my priority list for a few months. I remember back in October after a period of consistent training feeling on top of the world 🌏 I was excited to workout. I was proud of my body and it’s capabilities. Then... a crazy few months of travel kicked in. It’s been pretty none stop since November (I mean in February I was only in the UK for 5 days) 😅 During this manic time growing my brand, managing my business, producing content and maintaining my relationships have all come higher on my to do list than going to the gym. I haven’t lifted weights in weeks, and haven’t been to the gym consistently in months. And I’m not ashamed of that. Life ebbs and flows. Priorities change. Ultimately, it wasn’t what I wanted to give my time to 💁🏼‍♀️ But today I did a @balance_festival @farm_fitness fitness challenge and felt so weak - which I’ll blame that in part on my jet lag! 😂 But seriously, it was a big reminder. A kick up the bum. A motivational jolt. I WANT to fall in love with training again. I want to go to the gym. To push myself. To actually move my body regularly rather than sporadically 🏃🏼‍♀️ So this is me telling you that I’m going to try a little harder and push a little more. It’s time to get my fire back 🔥

Carrot Cake Oats Recipe 🥕 This is my favourite breakfast in the autumn months 🍂 ➡️ 1/2 cup oats ➡️ 3/4 cup plant based milk ➡️ 1/4 cup grated carrot ➡️ 1 tbsp maple syrup ➡️ 2 tbsp @aldiuk milled linseed (for extra fibre & omega 3) 💪🏼 ➡️ 1/4 tsp vanilla ➡️ 1/2 tsp cinnamon ➡️ A pinch of ground ginger and nutmeg ➡️ A handful of raisins and walnuts 😋 Just combine the ingredients in a bowl and leave overnight to soak. Serve in the morning with your toppings of choice ☀️ You can also modify this recipe: heating it in a pan for a warming breakfast or adding protein powder for a post-workout boost 💦

REPOST: hopefully this works for you guys now! 💗 Full Body Hotel Workout 💪🏼 I used a workout structure consisting of one triset per body part. The first exercise was a heavy 8 reps. The second exercise a moderate 15 reps. And the final a light 25 reps. I did three rounds of each triset. This 8,15,25 approach is a great way to cram a seriously tough workout in! 🔥 Thanks @gracefituk for the inspiration 😘Heres one of the leg trisets I did: 8 squats, 15 deadlifts, 25 jumping lunges 😷 Examples of other trisets I did include: ➡️ 8 Arnold press, 15 DB press, 25 face pulls ➡️ 8 banded pull ups, 15 cable rows, 25 lat pull overs ✅ Mix them up depending on the workout you're doing and let me know how you get on 💗

10 Minute Abs 🔥 Give this cheeky ab circuit a go next time you need to challenge your core 💪🏼 ➡️ 10 eccentric sit ups ➡️ 10 toe taps ➡️ 10 bicycle crunches ➡️ 30 second plank 💦 Just set a timer for 10 minutes and complete as many rounds as you can! Trust me, it’s a killer 😝

Pull Up Progressions 💪🏼 Operation get back my upper body strength is in full force! Today I did three chin up variations to help build up my strength in this movement. Please bear in mind that these videos are sped up! ➡️ Chin ups to failure. 3 rounds. I was aiming for 4-5 reps with FULL range of motion (no half reps here!). By the third round I could only do 2! 😰➡️ Eccentric Chin Ups. 3x2. Two super slow eccentric reps - just focusing on the downward phase of the movement. The first rep I aimed for 20+ seconds. The second rep I aimed for over 15 seconds 😷 ➡️ Chin Up Holds. 3x1. I aimed for a 10-15 second hold with a 90 degree angle at my elbows 👊🏼 I did these exercises at the beginning of my workout so I could give them maximum energy and effort 🤗 I'm wearing @adidasuk at @easygym 💗✌🏼

Nutella Protein Snowballs ❄️ Delicious, gluten free and high in protein! Pop in a food processor: 2 scoops @team_optimum chocolate whey protein, 1 cup hazelnuts, 1/4 cup @creativenaturesuperfoods cacao powder, 1/2 cup unsweetened almond milk and 1/3 cup coconut flour. Blend until it forms a thick paste. Then use your hands to form into balls and roll in desiccated coconut 👌 These are the perfect festive snack! You can use the code ROSVD10 for 10% off the @team_optimum website! You can find more recipes like this in my two ebooks linked on my profile 💕

Raw Vegan Protein Cookie Dough 🍪 Who has been following me since the days when @tallyrye and I would eat this stuff on a weekly basis? DAYUM it's good! I haven't eaten it in far too long! 😋 But since I'm cooking dinner for my girl @stephclairesmith tonight I figured I would make an old favourite. Now, don't be alarmed by what ingredients are included in this recipe. I promise it tastes BOMB 💣 These are rough estimates... I never really measure recipes, just eyeball them 👀 Pop in a blender: 1 can drained chickpeas, 2-3 heaping tbsp peanut butter, 2-3 tbsp maple syrup, 1 scoop vegan protein powder (I used @formnutrition), 1 tsp vanilla essence and a dash of milk (I used choc @oatly) 🙌🏼 Blend blend blend until smooth. You'll need to stir things up as you go along to help them combine. Scoop into a bowl and stir through chocolate chips or cacao nibs. BOSH! 💪🏼 Sounds weird. Tastes like crack. Trust me on this one guys 💗

Leg Day 🍑 This is the one superset you NEED to try 🔥 This morning I trained legs for the first time in a while and DAYUMMM it felt good! I included one of my favourite supersets for a glute burn ➡️ Heavy static lunges x8 per leg (focus on pushing up through the heel and keeping the knee stable - don’t let it wobble towards the centre - this stability uses your hip abductors)! ➡️ Elevated single leg glute bridges x10 per leg (squeeze at the top, push through the heels) 👌🏼 Complete the lunges and glute bridges on one leg before switching to the other for a real challenge. Bear in mind this video is sped up, so take your time! 💦 Wearing @adidasuk of course 💗

Chocolate protein cupcakes with a gooey peanut butter centre 😍 Combine: 1/2 cup chocolate protein powder, 1/2 cup flour (I used brown rice flour), 1/4 cup cocoa powder, 1 tsp baking powder, 170g Greek yoghurt, 1 egg, 1 egg white, 1/4 cup almond milk and 1/3 cup powdered stevia. Divide the mixture between 9 cupcake cases. Then pop half a tablespoon of peanut butter in each case and push it down so it is submerged. Then just bake them in a 180 degree oven for around 10-15 minutes until they're cooked through! They're best eaten fresh from the oven or you can microwave them to remelt the PB 🙊

HEALTHY APPLE CRUMBLE!😍 Firstly - over on my YouTube channel I just uploaded a video about how to stay healthy while travelling! 😘 Secondly, here's the recipe: For the base layer you need: 2 large cooking apples, 1 tsp cinnamon, 1/2 cup raisins, 1/2 tsp nutmeg, 1/2 tsp ground cloves, 1/4 cup water. Chop up the apples into bite size pieces. Put the apples in a bowl with the spices and raisins, stir until the apple is coated in spices. Heat up a non stick pan on a medium/high and pop in the apple/spice/raisin mix and add in 1/4 cup water. Simmer until the apples are softened - you might need to add more water depending on how long it takes. Once the apples are softened place them in the bottom of your crumble tray. 👍 For the crumble layer you need:1 cup whole rolled oats, 1/2 cup almond flour, 1/4 cup powdered stevia, 1/3 cup toasted almond flakes, 1/4 cup dessicated coconut, 1/2 tsp cinnamon. Combine the crumble ingredients and pour them over the top of the base layer. Bake at 180 degrees for about 20-25 minutes or until the crumble is beginning to turn golden brown 👌 This is also really nice with added blackberries or any other berry 😊 More recipes like this can be found in my ebooks linked on my profile! Nutella Cookies 💕 Yep, that's right... Cookies that literally taste like warm Nutella 🙊 Preheat the oven to 180 C. Mix together: 1/4 cup cocoa powder, 1 cup hazelnut flour/ground hazelnuts (you can buy this online or in healthfood shops!), 3 tbsp melted grass fed butter (or coconut oil), 2 tbsp honey, 1/2 tsp vanilla, 1/3 tsp baking powder, and a handful of dark chocolate chips. Spoon onto a baking sheet and bake for around 8-10 minutes! 👌

A massive thank you to @tarmarz for making my healthy chocolate pancakes 💕 The recipe is back in my feed but I will repost: 1/4 cup oat flour, 2 tbsp cocoa powder, 1 egg white, 4tbsp Greek yoghurt, a pinch of baking powder and a splash of almond milk. Mix the ingredients thoroughly, cook on a low to medium heat, flip them when bubbles appear on the surface, then stack em up 👌

Chocolate protein mug cake 👌 1 scoop chocolate protein powder, 1 tbsp cocoa powder, 1/4 tsp baking powder, 1 egg white and 2 tbsp milk. Mix the ingredients in a mug and microwave for about 45seconds to a minute. I topped mine with 2 tbsp melted crunchy peanut butter and some dedicated coconut 👍

Let's have a chat about social media. There has been a lot of discussion in the news, with many saying that it isn't reality and it can be a negative influence. My personal opinion is that social media is what you make it. If you spend your time scrolling through pictures of perfect girls with their perfect lives and compare yourselves to them - then it probably won't make you feel very good. It is so important to take everything you see online with a hefty pinch of salt. There is so much more that you don't see. You are only shown edited, filtered images of the highlights of people's lives. I am aware of the influence of my posts and I do try to be open and honest with you guys. Sure I will share aesthetically pleasing pictures but I also try to show the low points and not so glamorous parts of my life. In reality I am just the same as you. I have days where I don't have the motivation to train, days where I eat completely off plan, I have cellulite, I have bags under my eyes, I bite my nails, I cry. I often get told I have "the perfect life". Let me assure you that I don't, sure I have some amazing opportunities but remember... you just see the good bits. However - I think that if used correctly social media can be hugely positive. It can provide motivation to make positive changes, it can connect you with new people all over the world, allow you to share your passions and even lead to incredible friendships. Enjoy social media, avoid comparison and instead take inspiration 😘💕

Upper Body Workout 💪🏼 But first, see that slow-mo bit at the beginning of the video? That is me correcting my posture to protect my lower back, strengthen my core and ensure I use good form 🤗 Personally, my posture isn’t perfect. I have the common issue of our generation - an anterior pelvic tilt. Don’t be put off by those complex words, it basically just means my lower back arches in a mild state of “lordosis” which can put extra pressure through my spine 🤷🏼‍♀️ It is often caused my sitting at desks for an extended period of time. It isn’t the end of the world, I just need to consciously work towards correcting it through loosening my hips and strengthening my posterior chain (the back of my body - glutes, hammies, etc) 🍑 I also make sure that when I perform exercises that I tuck my hips under, correcting the anterior pelvic tilt, to avoid any further back issues 🤓 I can’t see all of you guys and comment on your posture but I can guess the vast majority of you will be in a similar situation to me, so I hope this helps 🙌🏼 Anyways - here’s the workout: ➡️ Barbell Row (3 second eccentric) x 10 ➡️ Barbell Press x10 ➡️ Barbell Curl x 10 ➡️ Plate Tricep Press x10 ➡️ Complete all 4 exercises back to back. Rest one minute and repeat 3 times 🔥 @Adidaswomen @un1t_london 💗

Yes my boyfriend is shorter than me. No it doesn’t bother me in the slightest 💁🏼‍♀️ I’ve lost count of the amount of DMs I’ve had from girls asking for advice, saying they’re taller than the guy they’re dating and feel self conscious about it. It makes me so sad 😔 Why?! WHY are we conditioned to believe the man must be taller? Who ever made that rule?! No one. Seriously, no one. It’s just some outdated social norm which I choose to ignore, and I think you should too 🙌🏼 Ant and I never even think about it. Love is love. Height doesn’t come into the equation 🙅🏼‍♀️ And if some narrow minded person points it out, we just laugh it off and feel sorry for them. The fact that they feel the need to judge us based on our height difference says more about them than it does about us 😂 Honestly guys, this is your ONE life. Don’t let some imaginary rule dictate your choices. If you find someone who really truly makes you happy, BE WITH THEM ❤️

Goodbye Barcelona 🇪🇸✌🏼 After the most whirlwind month of travel (5 countries in 4 weeks ✈️) I am returning to the UK for summer ☀️ How have I kept up my fitness routine during this time? The truth: not very well 😂 But I didn't intend to! On my business trips (NYC, Finland & Ireland) I made wise(ish) choices and tried to stay active with body weight workouts. However, when it came to my actual holidays (Ibiza & Barcelona) I just chilled the sweet eff out. I ate whatever the hell I wanted and I hardly trained. I just tried to stay active by walking (I've racked up 30,000 steps a day here in Barcelona!) 🏃🏼‍♀️ I absolutely loved the break, but I have to admit that I've missed looking after my body. It's definitely healthy to take time off, but it's also healthy to come back even more motivated than ever to nourish and move your body 🤗 Bring on the summer! 💗

Coconut Brownies 💕 Mix together: 3/4 cup Greek yoghurt, 1/2 cup cocoa powder, 1 egg, 1/3 cup powdered stevia, 1/2 cup oat flour, half a tsp baking powder and 1/2 cup shredded coconut. Then add milk (I used almond milk) until a nice thick consistency - I added around 1/4 cup. Pour into a lined tray and bake at 180 degrees C for around 20 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean. ☺️

The ULTIMATE Healthy Cookie Recipe 😍 Gluten free! This is my favourite cookie recipe I've ever created. They literally taste like heaven. Low carb and full of healthy fats. Mix together 1 and 1/4 cup almond flour, 3 tbsp melted coconut oil or grass fed butter (I recommend Kerrygold), 2 tbsp honey, 1 tsp vanilla, a pinch of baking powder and a handful of dark chocolate chips (use raisins to make dairy free). Once combined plop onto a baking sheet and bake at 180 for 10 minutes. They will be slightly soft when they come out the oven. Leave to cool and then devour them. This recipe makes a small batch, and can be found along with lots of other yummy recipes in my first ebook (link on my profile) 💕

Put down your phone ☎️ One of my goals this year is to disconnect from technology on a regular basis. This is particularly challenging as my job relies on social media use. However I have found that by spending less time on my phone, not only am I more productive, but I'm less stressed and I connect more with those around me. Here's some things I have been doing: 1️⃣ Turning my phone on airplane mode when I'm with someone. This allows me to give them my full attention and shows my respect for them. Nothing is worse than trying to talk to someone and they are constantly looking at their phone. 2️⃣ I enjoy moments without capturing them. I look at a beautiful view without taking a picture, share a funny moment without tweeting about it or watch a concert without videoing it. It's nice to have memories that are just for me and whoever I'm with - rather than for social media. 3️⃣ Looking up. When I'm out and about, especially when I'm walking around London or commuting, I make sure to avoid mindlessly scrolling on my phone. I take in my surroundings. The world is pretty amazing when you take the time to look at it. 🌍 For more tips about how to be mindful, check out my latest blog post - link on my profile 💕

Jumping Lunges: Beginner, Intermediate and Advanced Variations 👊🏼 I feel like jumping lunges are featured in so many workouts, as if they're super easy and accessible. In reality they're really tough and can be high impact on your body. So I thought I would show you a few variations for if you're new to this challenging exercise and want to build up your abilities ➡️ Beginner: Alternating lunges ➡️ Intermediate: 4x shuffles then 2 jump lunges ➡️ Advanced: Regular jump lunges 💪🏼 You can also try all three exercises while holding a TRX if you struggle with stability ☺️ These are a great addition to a bodyweight circuit or a HIIT workout 🔥 It's also worth noting that this exercise isn't may not be suitable for you if you have tight hips/hammies and can't do a lunge with a full range of motion, or if you struggle with high impact exercises. Always listen to your body 🙌🏼 Wearing head to toe @adidasuk 💕

Peanut Butter Protein Chocolates 🍫 Melt 50g extra dark chocolate with a tbsp coconut oil, and then mix in half a scoop of chocolate protein powder (@team_optimum of course!). Pour this into the bottom of an ice cube tray in a thin layer, then freeze for 30 mins until set. Pop a teeny bit of peanut butter in each mould and then pour over another chocolate/coconut oil/protein powder mix (the same ingredients and measures as the first layer). Freeze until set, gobble them up!

It's time for a ramble 💁 These past few days with @cleanfitlifestyle and @healthyfitvic have been amazing. These two girls are the most fun, caring and empowering people I know. 💕 We had a lot of long discussions regarding health and fitness, and it's lead me to want to make some changes. I've realised that I want my training and nutrition to focus less on aesthetics and more on function, strength, fitness and most of all - pleasure. I want to go on a 10km run if I fancy it and not worry about losing muscle. I want to lift heavy and get stronger, but I also want to do sprints and plyometric training. I want to fuel my body appropriately so I'm full of energy, and not worry about having abs. I don't want to feel like I have to conform to others ideas of what is the right and wrong way to train and eat. Don't get me wrong, I'm still going to lift because I absolutely love it and the changes it's made to my body. It is my favourite form of training! However, I'm going to be more flexible with my approach to fitness and nutrition; and care less about how I look and more about how I feel 👍

Feeling Energy Fit 💪 As you guys know over the past two weeks I have taken a challenge to try and reduce the energy waste around my house using my smart meter. Through tracking my energy use and seeing how much I am spending in pounds and pence I have been able to make sustainable swaps, which benefit me and the planet 🌎 These include things like switching off lights, turning devices off standby, cooking more one pan meals and taking a minute off my shower time 💦 (If you want to hear more quick tips then there is a full post with all my recommendations on my blog!) 🤓 Hopefully seeing my journey has inspired you to get more savvy with your energy waste and get a smart meter installed - everyone can get one, even if you rent your home! Just contact your energy supplier ❤️✌🏼

Lifting Weights 💪🏼 The one form of training which has stayed consistently in my routine since the very beginning. Admittedly, my love for lifting weights has wavered over the past few years. I've had times when I loved it and times when I just wasn't feeling it. Times when I lifted 5 days a week and times when I lifted once a week. And I just want to say... that's ok. Fitness is for LIFE. You can't be expected the train the same way forever. Quite frankly, that would be boring! That's why I always love to mix it up. I do classes. I do gymnastics. I do boxing. I run. I lift. I'm up for trying anything! I dabble and I'm not ashamed of that. I think sometimes you see the girls on Instagram all lifting weights and you think that's what you HAVE to do. If you love it, go for it. And if you don't, don't force yourself. Enjoyment leads to sustainability so prioritise finding forms of training which you actually look forward to doing! 🙌🏼 I personally have fallen back in love with weights recently. It makes me feel so damn strong and empowered. The feeling of satisfaction when you push yourself to lift a little heavier is incredible. Plus I feel reassured knowing that I am supporting my bone health too 💪🏼 Wearing @adidasuk at @fitnessfirstuk 💗

HOW TO MAKE THICK CREAMY SMOOTHIES 😍🙌🏼 I get asked all the time how I achieve this texture with my protein smoothies. There are a few key components: 1️⃣ Use a whole FROZEN banana. This is essential. 2️⃣ Use LOTS of ice. 3️⃣ Don't add much milk. Less than you think! ✅ You will need to stop the blender as you make it to shake it up and ensure everything is blended. It takes a little extra time but it's worth it. 😋 This particular smoothie is made from: 1 scoop @vivolife salted caramel protein, 1 frozen banana, 3 large frozen strawberries, a dash of oat milk and lots of ice 🙌🏼 If you're looking for more smoothie recipes check out my book, linked on my profile 💗

What weights should you lift? 🤔 Underneath every single workout video I post I get this question and I want to answer it for you 🙌🏼 Guys... I cannot tell you what weight to lift! I don't know you. I don't know your training history. I haven't seen you move. Without this information (and more) I can't prescribe a weight. Which is why I never share weights on my posts. What works for me may not work for you, and vice versa 💪🏼 What you need to do, is pick a weight which challenges YOU in the rep range you're working in. For example if it's squats for 3 sets of 10 reps. You need to find a weight which leaves you really struggling to complete the last few reps, but able to maintain good form throughout 👌🏼 For some that may be bodyweight for some that may be with 100kg on your back! 😝 The main thing to remember is to PUSH yourself! Don't pick a weight you know you can comfortably lift. It needs to be uncomfortable, as that's where change happens and strength develops. Similarly, try not to use the same weight over and over for months on end. Focus on upping those weights and reps over time. I have a full blog post on my website on this principle of "progressive overload" so check it out if you're confused 🤓 And finally - please don't compare your weights on day one to someone else's weights on day 300 of their journey. It takes time to build up strength and every expert started as a beginner. Embrace the journey 🙌🏼 Wearing @adidas 💗

Constantly humbled by history 😍 This trip is everything I needed and more. I travel extensively for work and I have a tendency to tie work into my personal holidays too. As a result I am on my laptop creating content late into the evening when I’m away with my boyfriend. He never complains, he’s too lovely, but I know he wants me to be able to switch off like he does. That’s why I am making a conscious effort on this trip to do just that. I’m not blogging. Not vlogging. Not pressuring myself to capture fitness content for Instagram. Not obsessively replying to emails within minutes of receiving them. Nothing. And it’s bloody INCREDIBLE. It’s so refreshing to capture content because I want to, not because I need to. I know it sounds silly, but it’s true 😂 As a blogger you can put unrealistic expectations on yourself and expect your career to fall apart the moment you stop posting 🙈 Don’t get me wrong, I realise how blessed my job is, its a dream I’ve chased and worked towards for years. I feel gratitude for my job everyday. But I still need time to step back and switch off 🙌🏼 So for now, I hope you stick with me while I take this much needed mental break 🌍💙

Post-Workout Smoothie 😋 Want to know how to to make the thickest, creamiest protein shake that resembles ice cream? I got your back 😉 Here is what I made this morning: ➡️ Oat milk - the key is not to add too much of this! ➡️ 1 scoop vegan protein (I'm trying lots of brands at the moment, this one is @missfitsnutrition) ➡️ Agave ➡️ cocoa or cacao powder (mine is @kaizenliving) ➡️ 2 frozen bananas - fresh don't work the same! ➡️ Ice ✅ Blend it all - I use a @ninjakitchenuk. You'll need to shake it half way through blending as it's super thick! Then you can sip it through a reusable straw or eat it with a spoon 🥄 Enjoy! 💗

“Be the change you want to see in the world” 🌍 Today I took part in a @sustainablecoastlineshawaii beach clean 🌴 It was empowering and motivating yet heartbreaking 💔 We collected overwhelming amounts of ocean plastic from a single stretch of beach. Hundreds of metres of fishing rope, thousands of water bottles and countless micro plastics. It was piling up in mountains 😩 We NEED to come together to make this stop. Marine plastic is destroying our oceans and the creatures that live there. And the harsh reality? If the ocean dies, we die. We rely on it for every second breath we take 🌊 The greatest threat to our planet is the belief that someone else is going to save it. We need to stop looking to others for solutions, instead let’s come together and BE the solution. As @chelseykorus says “we are the ones we have been waiting for” 🙌🏼 You can see so much more of my experiences today on my Instagram stories, including a few tears 😢 And I have a super informative article on my blog about how we can all work together to fight ocean plastic: www.zannavandijk.co.uk 🐬 I really strongly encourage you to read it! 🤓Thank you @adidas @wanderlustfest @parley.tv for giving me to opportunity to contribute to positive change 🌱 I’m so proud to say the @adidas outfit I’m wearing in these photos is made from recycled marine plastic; and this is just the beginning 💚 Photo: @pabloshirley 📸

Chickpea Blondies 😍 this is an old favourite of mine, but the recipe is really far back in my feed, so I thought it deserved a repost 👍 1 can of chickpeas (drained, rinsed and fried), 1/4 cup peanut butter, 1/4 cup oats, 1/2 cup dark chocolate chips or cacao nibs, 1 tsp baking powder, 1 tbsp vanilla extract, 3/4 cup powdered stevia, 100ml unsweetened almond milk. Blend all the ingredients except the milk and chocolate chips. Then slowly add the milk until the mixture is thick and creamy (you might not need all the milk!). Stir in the chocolate chips. Pour into a lined tin and bake at 200 degrees for around 15 minutes. Leave to cool and set 👍

My Journey: 62kg to 72kg 💪🏼The scales aren't always the best way to judge progress 😝 I had always been skinny...then I went to university. I lived off a diet of pizza and vodka. By the end of second year I had become "skinny fat". I had gained a stone but I was slim and untoned. I then used various fad diets such as low carb, low fat and low calorie approaches to get myself looking like the photo on the left. I was 62kg and unfit. I couldn't run for the bus without panting. Thankfully I soon became tired of being tired. Of yoyo diets. Of hating exercise. I made an Instagram account and I decided I wanted to try lifting weights like the girls I followed. This began a 5 year journey to where I am now in the right hand photo. I'm 72kg - yes 10 kilos heavier - and I'm fitter, healthier and happier than ever before. It was a slow process of self education. I went through phases of bodybuilding, IIFYM, paleo... everything! You name it, I tried it. There was A LOT of trial and error. But a couple of years ago I reached a point where I finally achieved my own personal balance. I don't fit into a box or a label. I train flexibly, in ways I enjoy. I lift weights. I do cardio. I play around with headstands. I like to try new classes, box and do crossfit on occasion. I train to get fitter and stronger, not to look a certain way. I eat mostly plant based and completely intuitively. I listen to my body and nourish it with good quality wholesome food. I don't put pressure on myself to train or eat a certain way. And most importantly? I've gone from regularly criticising my body to loving myself unapologetically. That is the biggest progress of all. Now, I am full of endless motivation to train hard and eat well because I love myself! And I encourage you guys to love yourself too 😘 If you want to learn more about achieving a balanced lifestyle check out my book Strong which is linked on my profile 💕

BOOTY BLASTER 🍑😷 I learned this trick from @thepilatespt and it's a killer! (Note the video is sped up 4x). 👊🏼 Pop a looped resistance band around your knees and take a bridge position. Put tension on the band and lift your hips an inch off the floor. Pulse your knees outwards 10 times and then hold at the widest position for 5 seconds. Lift another inch and repeat. Lift and repeat 4-5 times until you reach a full bridge. Hold for 10 seconds on the last one. OUCH! 🔥 I like to add this to the end of my leg days and do it 2-3 times. The burn is real! 😝 Outfit: @adidasuk and gym: @thelomaxway 💕

Time for a little story 💭 A year ago today I moved to London. I came down to do my personal training course with @trainfitnessint to further my knowledge prior to a masters degree in sports nutrition. So, I got a temporary room and intended to be here for 6 weeks... I never left! London grabbed me with both hands and sucked me in. I started working as a PT, got signed to @w_modelmgmt and worked on my blog. It was a big risk and a stark contrast from living on a farm in Yorkshire. I didn't know where this was going to take me but I worked my arse off. Soon enough opportunities came knocking. As things developed, I went from 7 days a week PT down to 5 and now down to 2. I currently have two companies and my own activewear collection releasing soon. I am the co-founder of @thegirlgains. I speak. I write. I film. I do shoots. I train people. I never imagined this time last year when I moved to this city that my life would change this much. My masters degree has been put on hold and I'm quite literally chasing my dreams. I have no idea where this will take me and I'm not naive... I know that the industry is fickle and that I may fail, but I will try my damn hardest not to! 👊🏼

Why do I live a healthy lifestyle? Why do I train hard and eat a balanced diet? 🤔 Because I love my body. I love my body enough to want to nourish it with wholesome foods and strengthen it with exercise. Not because I hate my body. Not because I hate how I look. Not as punishment or out of guilt. I find that when you live a healthy lifestyle out of self-love rather than self-loathing, it becomes so much easier to enjoy your journey along the way. I put my focus on how I feel and how I perform rather than solely on how I look. I don't pick myself apart or criticise my body, I admire how strong and capable it is. It is so incredible that I have the ability and strength to push myself hard inside and outside the gym. I celebrate my body and everything it can do, and I hope you guys can do the same with yours 😘 Wearing @activeinstyle 💕

“Zanna, your life is so perfect” “Life goals” “I want your life” 💬 These are comments I have received over the past week, and they worry me 😥 It is so easy to see someone’s social media accounts and assume they’re always happy. Always positive. Always succeeding. But please remember that social media, and Instagram in particular, is a highlight reel. My stories are 90 seconds out of a 24 hour day and my posts are filtered snapshot of my reality 📸 Don’t get me wrong, I bloody love my life and in general, I am extremely happy. However, my life is far from perfect 🙅🏼 I fail, a lot. I get stressed and overwhelmed, a lot. I have issues with my friendships, relationships and family. I don’t always succeed and I’m not always happy. And that is ok, I’m human 💁🏼 If you ever find yourself feeling low or demoralised by viewing my content, maybe I’m not the blogger for you. I don’t ever want to make you uninspired or unhappy, and if I do then please don’t be afraid to unfollow me. Your happiness is of the utmost importance to me and I won’t be offended ❤️ If you want to hear more about the topic of social media comparison then check out the latest @thegirlgains podcast episode. Glute and Hamstring Burner 🔥 This morning I finished off my leg session with @Hirstlucie with this combo ☠️ A good morning into curtsey lunges 🍑 The key points to note with these exercises are: ➡️ Good mornings. Keep your back straight and core engaged, hinging from the hips. On the upward movement, consciously keep your knees stable and don't let them buckle inwards - this will really fire up your hip abductors. ➡️ Curtsey lunges: take a deep diagonal stride and ensure when you come up out of the lunge that you use your front leg, pushing through the heel as much as possible 👌🏼 Try doing 3 sets of 12 reps. Tag me if you give it a go! ☺️ Wearing @adidaswomen 💕

Reality Check ✌🏼️These two photos are taken seconds apart. The one on the left is posed and the one on the right is when I relax 🙆🏼 Instagram photos are a finely tuned combination of angles, lighting and filters. In reality the people in them don't look like that 90% of the time. I only have abs in the morning. In certain lighting. When I lift my boobs. And squint a little. But I can damn well take a photo which makes it look like they're are popping 😂 In reality, I just look like a normal person. I don't walk around flexing 💪🏼 It is inevitable that we compare ourselves to those we follow on social media. We all do it. What matters is that we take what we see with a hefty pinch of salt. Don't try and look like the girls on Instagram. Don't try and look like me. Instead, try to be the best version of YOU! 💕

"The most attractive thing about you should have less to do with your face and body, and more to do with your heart and how you treat other people" ✌🏼 Just a reminder to not place your self-worth on your appearance alone. Think about your best friend, why do you love them? I bet it's for their personality, their intelligence, their banter or their caring nature. Not their thigh gap or flat stomach. And your best friend? They love YOU because of who you are. Not how you look. You are so SO much more than that 💗

This this this 🙏🏼🙌🏼 I can't express this enough. We are all guilty of comparing ourselves to others. You might think "why aren't I as fit as her?" but that girl has probably been working hard to get fit for months or even years. Maintaining a lean physique or getting into amazing shape takes graft, graft that people often don't show or share. If you're struggling, don't forget that the people you're following have their struggles to. They just might not show them. Please remember that we all started somewhere. The people you follow on Instagram we're not born with bulging biceps or a rippling six pack. Every master was once a novice. Progress takes time, it can be slow and frustrating. Half the battle is sticking with it when you feel disheartened. But your journey is unique to you - if you're following someone who seems to be going from strength to strength then be happy for them. Be inspired. But don't compare yourself. You will have your moment, you will reach your goals. You just need to believe in yourself, work towards your goals and wait until you reach your chapter 20. 💕

🌟 Banana Chocolate Protein Bars 🌟 You need: 1 scoop chocolate protein powder, 2 scoops banana protein powder, 170g Greek yoghurt, 2 eggs, 1/2 cup flour (I used oat flour), 1/4 cup cocoa powder, 1/4 cup honey and a handful of chocolate chips. Literally just mix the ingredients, put into a lined/greased tin, and bake at 180 degrees for around 15 minutes. You can change the flavour of the protein powders to whatever you fancy, but I love the combination of banana and chocolate 👍

"Textbook technique does not exist" 💭 I had a really interesting discussion with @mikeleept this week about the notion of "perfect form" on an exercise. Of course there are basic principles surrounding each exercise and we shouldn't be modifying them in such a way to increase the risk of injury: However, ultimately every movement should be adapted to the individual. To their needs, their goals, their physical limitations, their injuries, their mobility. There are SO many factors which play a part. Take the bear crawl 🐻 This exercise can be performed a multitude of ways which vary in difficulty and which call upon using different muscle groups more heavily. Which one you choose is personal to you, your goals and your abilities 💪🏼 This is why it is essential to ADAPT your training to suit you. To be aware of your body. To personalise your program and your exercises to consider any limitations you have. Train smart and train safe guys 💗 Wearing @adidasuk 💃🏼

Egg Fried 'Rice': 3 tbsp coconut oil, 2 garlic cloves, 1/3-1/2 a head of cauliflower (grated), a portion of cooked prawns, soy sauce, half a chilli, 1 egg, 1 large spring onion. Put the oil in a wok, add the garlic and chilli and simmer for a few mins. Then add the grated cauliflower and coat in the oil for 1 min. Add the spring onion and 1 tbsp soy sauce and stir until it looks golden. Add the prawns and cook them through. Make a 'well' in the middle of the wok and add the egg, let it cook for a few seconds then stir it through the mixture. Serve and garnish with herbs of your choice ☺

Booty Building 🍑 I know everyone wants to grow a peachy tush, myself included. However there are more benefits to glute training than just aesthetics. In our modern sedentary lifestyles where we spend a lot of time sat down, our hips tighten and our glutes weaken. This can lead to imbalances, discomfort and injuries; and weaken your posterior chain. It's super important to strengthen your glutes and stretch out your hips 👌🏼 Here is one of my favourite glute supersets: 1️⃣ Wide leg RDLs x 10 2️⃣ Sumo Kettlebell Deadlifts x10 🙌🏼 As you can see, I work very slowly through a full range of motion and really focus on engaging my glutes to get maximum activation and results 🍑 Outfit: @adidasuk at @fitnessfirstuk 💕

Reality check: I’m not as strong as I used to be 💪🏼 I used to be able to deadlift 100kg for reps. Today I struggled to do 70kg for 5x5. And that’s ok 💃🏼 My training structure over the past 6 months has gone out the window. My life has been all over the place and I’ve let go of the rigid lifting routine I used to have. Luckily, fitness comes in many different forms and I don’t judge my worth by the weights I can push around. I used to lift 5 days a week. Now I am lucky if I do it twice. Instead I work with the limited time I have. Somethings I weight train. Sometimes I run. Sometimes I do body weight circuits. I mix it up. I may not be able to pick up 100kg but I feel fitter than ever and I’m loving the flexibility of my approach. It’s enjoyable and achievable for me, and ultimately that’s what matters! 🙌🏼 The lesson? Don’t be afraid to change your workout routine. Don’t be tied to one form of training forever. Life would be boring if we never changed, developed and evolved. Sometimes life throws curveballs at us and we have to adapt. Embrace it. You never know what passion you might discover 💗

That concentration face 😂😂😂 Seriously though, this is SUCH a good shoulder burner 🔥 It's called a rep ladder, a technique @adamwillis_lbp taught me 💪🏼 Complete one full dumbbell shoulder Press, then a half rep. Then do a second full rep, and then TWO half reps. Repeat, adding a half rep each time! By the end you're doing 1 full rep followed by 8+ half reps. Ouch. ☠️ Aim for 8-10 reps for 3 sets and feel the FIYYAAAHHHH 😂😅 Wearing @adidasuk 💗

😍 Apple and Cinnamon Protein Muffins 😍 Since you all liked yesterday's picture so much, here is the recipe as promised! Preheat the oven to 180c/350f. Mix together: 1 cup oats, 1 cup almond flour, 2 scoops @team_optimum vanilla whey, 1/2 cup unrefined coconut sugar, 1/2 cup melted coconut oil, 4 eggs, 1 tbsp baking powder, 1 small apple chopped very finely, 2 tbsp apple pie spice, and 1/4 cup unsweetened almond milk. The apple pie spice mix can be substituted for a homemade mixture of cinnamon and nutmeg 👌 Thoroughly combine all the ingredients. Pour this into muffin cases and bake for around 15-20 minutes until cooked through. This mixture makes around 8 muffins. The frosting is a mixture of plain Greek yoghurt, honey and cinnamon. I topped my muffins with chopped almonds and chia seeds 👍 You can use the code ROSVD10 for a discount on @team_optimum products, and more recipes like this can be found in my ebook which is linked on my profile 💕

Sri Lanka Beach Clean 🌊 Tag a friend you want to do a beach clean with 👯‍♀️ This is how much plastic we collected on a 50m stretch of beach in just 20 minutes; right in the heart of in a secluded National Park 🌴 The locals say that fresh plastic washes up every day from the Indian Ocean in overwhelming quantities 😿 This ocean plastic has serious consequences, damaging ecosystems and harming wildlife🙅🏼‍♀️ So what can we do to fight this? ➡️ Pick it up. If you see plastic on a beach, or in any area of natural beauty, please pick it up and dispose of it properly. (Recycling if possible!). This can help stop it causing further harm to coastal wildlife. ➡️ Ultimately, clean beaches start at home. Take a look at your daily life and see where you’re consuming plastic and implement some sustainable swaps to reduce this. I have a whole blog post on my website with tips and tricks for this so please do give it a read. A great place to start is with reusable products like water bottles, coffee ups and straws ➡️ Instigate wider change. Can you make an impact in your workplace? Can your office swap disposable cups for reusable mugs? Make it happen! 🌊 You can see more of our beach clean on my instagram stories - it’s pretty heartbreaking though, I warn you 💔

Target Those Hamstrings 👊🏼 Often when we train legs, our hamstrings can get neglected. We need to show them some love too! They help to support your posterior chain and also target that tough to tone "back of the leg" area which I get asked about all the time! 👌🏼 Here are three of my favourite hamstring exercises: ➡️ Good mornings ➡️ Romanian deadlifts ➡️ Staggered stance Romanian deadlifts (to isolate each leg) 💪🏼 The main thing here is to keep your core engaged and your back straight. Try completing these exercises next to a mirror so you can check your form throughout the movement. Go for 3-4 sets of 10-12 reps, nice and slowly (this video is sped up) 😘 Outfit: @activeinstyle @adidasuk 💕

What are my values? I get asked this all the time, and I used to struggle to give a clear cut answer. Knowing your values takes time, life experience and self-reflection. I have grown to realise that what really matters to me is strength, positivity and happiness. I want the strength to take on life, face new challenges, overcome setbacks and push myself to achieve my dreams. I choose positivity. I consciously stay positive, avoid negative vibes and try to find the good in every day. And of course, happiness. Isn't this everyone’s ultimate goal? I believe that if you choose to be present in the moment and to be positive, grateful and mindful it is so much easier to find your version of happiness. These are the three principles I strive to keep in the forefront of my mind on a daily basis. As you can tell, I am passionate about my values. Which is why I am so excited to be teaming up with @theofficialpandora and their ESSENCE collection. The collection is based around charms which represent your personal journey of self-improvement and your key values. I chose the Strength, Positivity and Happiness charms. I will be working with @theofficialpandora over the next few weeks to share my values more deeply with you, so keep your eyes peeled 💕

I preach on a regular basis that you shouldn't compare yourself to those you follow on social media. That you should just focus on yourself and your journey. But you know what? I'm guilty of it too. I look at the girls I follow and think "their lives are so fun", while I sit at home in my dressing gown doing work on a Saturday night. I look at the girls running marathons and think "they're so fit!" while I struggle to complete a 5km. I'm the same as you, I do it, we all do. However, if there's one thing I've learnt in the past few years of being a blogger; its that this isn't our whole life. It's a snapshot. You don't know what goes on behind the scenes. We snapchat the best bits, the highlights of our day. We Instagram photos which are filtered within an inch of their lives. We focus on the fun stuff, not the graft; and we work damn hard behind the scenes. In reality, we all have good and bad days. We all cry sometimes. We all have our insecurities. And quite frankly, we all have our own shit to deal with 😂👌🏼 So next time you find yourself comparing yourself to someone on social media, remember that we are all human 😘 Photo: @jonpaynephoto 💕

Gooey black bean brownies 😍 1 tin of black beans (rinsed and dried thoroughly), 1/2 cup oats, 2 tbsp cocoa powder, pinch of salt, 1/4cup honey, 2 tbsp stevia, 1/4 cup coconut oil, 2 tsp vanilla extract, pinch of baking powder, 2/3 cup choc chips. You literally just blend all the ingredients together except the chips. Then stir in the chips and put into a lined baking tin. Bake at 180 degrees for 15-20 mins. Leg and booty sculpting 🍑 This exercise BURNS! Grab a kettlebell and hold it close to your chest, place your feet wide apart with toes pointing forward. Try doing 12 slow controlled reps each direction. Let me know how you get along! Raspberry Coconut Breakfast Muffins 😍 These are super simple and great for on-the-go! In a big bowl chuck in: 1 and 1/2 cup oats, 2 eggs, 3/4 cup Greek yoghurt, 1/2 cup desiccated coconut, 1 tsp baking powder, 1/3 cup powdered sweetener (e.g. Stevia), and 1/4 cup almond milk. Mix mix mix. Then gently stir in 3/4 cup raspberries. Spray muffin liners with cooking spray to prevent sticking. Pour the mixture into muffin trays - it makes between 6-8 muffins. Pop some extra raspberries on top if you're feeling fancy. Bake at 180c for around 15-20 minutes. Demolish them 👌

Lemon Raisin Protein Pancakes 💕 This is an adaption of a pancake recipe by @cleanfitlifestyle 👍 In a blender/food processor mix together: 1 scoop @team_optimum vanilla protein, 1/2 cup oats or 1/3 cup oat flour, a pinch of baking powder, 2 tbsp Greek yoghurt, 1 egg white, 1 tbsp coconut flour, 3-4 tbsp of almond milk and the zest of half a lemon (or a dash of lemon extract). Once thoroughly combined add in a handful of raisins and stir through. Cook on a medium to low heat and flip when bubbles appear on the surface. Then just stack em up high 👌(p.s. Let's take a moment to appreciate how much effort I put into the presentation of these 😂)

Amen 🙌 What we post on social media is what we want to portray to others. We don't often show our low moments, our slip ups or our 'bad bits'. We only post photos which are flattering, and it might take 20 selfies to find one we like. We only post our healthy meals or ones which look pretty. We only talk about positive body image and self confidence. I admit I do this myself. I talk about positivity, when sometimes I get down and feel negative. I will only post certain selfies and sometimes I get self conscious and delete them later. I am not perfect, no one is perfect. So many of us try and portray a perfect image of ourselves, one which often isn't real. Don't compare yourself to those you follow on social media, and please don't compare yourself to me! 💕

Banana Chocolate Protein Muffins with Chocolate Peanut Butter Protein Frosting 😍👌 I posted this recipe a few days ago over in my Facebook page (Zanna van Dijk) and it went down super well! So I thought I would share it on here too 💕 Preheat the oven to 180c/350f. In a bowl combine: 2 large mashed bananas, 2 scoops @team_optimum chocolate whey (use the code ROSVD10 for 10% off!), 3 eggs, 2 egg whites, 1 tsp baking powder, 1/4 cup cocoa powder, 1/4 cup almond flour, and 1/4 cup almond milk. Pour into greased muffin cases and bake for around 15-20 minutes until cooked through. For the frosting mix in a bowl: 1/4 cup chocolate PPB or PB2, 1/4 cup unsweetened almond milk, 1 scoop @team_optimum chocolate whey protein, and 2 tbsp coconut flour. Pop this on top of the cooked cupcakes and devour them! YUM! 💕 More recipes like this can be found in the ebook linked on my profile 😘
